3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkarnataka-a-potentially-historic-election%5C%22%3EKarnataka%3A%20A%20Potentially%20Historic%20Election%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%202023%20Karnataka%20assembly%20polls%2C%20the%20JD(S)%20fielded%2022%20Muslim%20candidates.%20It%20also%20vowed%20to%20restore%20the%204%25%20reservation%20for%20Muslims%20that%20was%20revoked%20by%20the%20Basavaraj%20Bommai%20government.%20But%20it%20now%20seems%20that%20Muslim%20voters%20saw%20through%20Kumaraswamy%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csecular%E2%80%9D%20facade%20and%20voted%20en%20masse%20for%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%2022%20candidates%20were%20defeated%20and%20many%20even%20lost%20their%20deposit.%20The%20JD(S)%20was%20wiped%20out%20in%20the%20elections.%20This%20is%20despite%20it%20having%20enjoyed%20support%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%20in%20the%20Old%20Mysore%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fkarnataka-election-results-jds-decimated-in-its-vokkaliga-stronghold%2Farticleshow%2F100220168.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewon%2041%20of%20the%2061%20seats%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20across%20seven%20districts%20that%20are%20part%20of%20the%20region.%20Its%20victories%20came%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20JD(S)%2C%20and%20D.K.%20Shivakumar%20emerged%20as%20the%20new%20Vokkaliga%20strongman.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20JD(S)%20also%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20the%20BJP%20on%20its%20own%20in%20the%20Vokkaliga%20belt%20in%20this%20election.%20Of%20the%20just%20over%20one%20crore%20votes%20polled%20in%2061%20seats%20in%20the%20region%2C%20the%20BJP%20polled%2024%2C60%2C429%20votes%20%E2%80%93%20just%20six%20lakh%20less%20than%20the%20JD(S)%E2%80%99s%2030%2C35%2C584%20votes%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fbjp-closes-gap-to-jds-in-old-mysuru-region%2Farticleshow%2F100237635.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20dismal%20performance%20not%20only%20put%20a%20question%20mark%20on%20Kumaraswamy%E2%80%99s%20leadership%2C%20but%20on%20the%20very%20existence%20of%20the%20JD(S).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuestion%20of%20survival%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumaraswamy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Fi-stood-by-muslims-but-they-didnt-support-jds-says-kumaraswamy-2698811%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eblamed%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20on%20Muslims%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhd-kumaraswamys-party-joins-bjp-led-nda-alliance-4414032%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallied%20with%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%202024%20election%20within%20four%20months.%20He%20also%20hinted%20at%20the%20possibility%20of%20another%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fcongress-govt-may-fall-in-karnataka-claims-jds-leader-hd-kumaraswamy-11702224291013.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COperation%20Lotus%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Ftwo-jds-muslim-leaders-resign-following-alliance-with-bjp-in-karnataka%2Farticle67338938.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20Muslim%20leaders%20quit%20the%20party%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20over%20its%20decision%20to%20ally%20with%20the%20BJP.%20Syed%20Shafiullah%2C%20state%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20JD(S)%2C%20said%20the%20party%20stood%20on%20principles%20of%20secularism%20while%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%9Cpreaches%2C%20propagates%20and%20acts%20on%20%5Ba%5D%20communal%20agenda%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FWATCH%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23WATCH%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20Bengaluru%3A%20On%20his%20resignation%20from%20the%20party%2C%20JDS%20Karnataka%20Vice%20President%20Syed%20Shafiulla%20Saheb%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20with%20the%20party%20for%20the%20past%2030%20years.%20Our%20party%20stand%20on%20secular%20credentials%2C%20and%20we%20have%20always%20propagated%20the%20principles%20of%20Secularism%20to%20the%20voters%2C%20and%20to%20the%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FS2okhgTmA0%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FS2okhgTmA0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20ANI%20(%40ANI)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1705808247620518211%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2024%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20typical%20pettiness%2C%20Kumaraswamy%20questioned%20the%20contributions%20of%20Muslim%20leaders%20to%20his%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20H.D.%20Deve%20Gowda%2C%20Kumaraswamy%E2%80%99s%20father%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20former%20chief%2C%20believes%20that%20by%20rallying%20its%20original%20support%20base%20behind%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20JD(S)%20can%20rejuvenate%20its%20electoral%20gains%3B%20but%20it%20might%20end%20up%20bolstering%20the%20BJP%20in%20its%20own%20bastion.%20Now%2C%20with%20the%20JD(S)%E2%80%99s%20support%2C%20the%20BJP%20might%20in%202024%20achieve%20its%20distant%20dream%20of%20gaining%20a%20foothold%20in%20the%20Mysore%20belt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumaraswamy%E2%80%99s%20changing%20stance%20is%20known%20in%20political%20circles%20and%20he%20is%20euphemistically%20called%20%E2%80%9Ckingmaker%E2%80%9D%20during%20every%20election%20in%20Karnataka.%20During%20the%202023%20assembly%20election%2C%20when%20asked%20if%20he%20will%20be%20the%20kingmaker%20after%20the%20polls%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20fractured%20mandate%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkarnataka%2F2023%2Fapr%2F20%2Fnot-a-kingmaker-but-will-be-king-says-hdk-2567561.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKumaraswamy%20replied%20pompously%20that%20he%20will%20be%20the%20king%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESecular%20kingmaker%20to%20(saffron)%20pawn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20Kumaraswamy%20is%20a%20sudden%20neo-convert%20and%20is%20doubling%20down%20on%20the%20Hindutva%20plank.%20The%20Kumaraswamy-led%20JD(S)%20has%20hobnobbed%20with%20the%20BJP%20earlier%20too%2C%20having%20formed%20the%20government%20twice%20since%20its%20inception%20in%201999%20as%20a%20breakaway%20faction%20from%20the%20Janata%20Dal.%20Gathering%20its%20strength%20from%20the%20Vokkaliga%20belt%20in%20southern%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20JD(S)%20has%20been%20playing%20the%20role%20of%20kingmaker%20since%202004.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%202004%20election%2C%20the%20JD(S)%20backed%20the%20Congress%20in%20a%20post-poll%20alliance%2C%20following%20which%20Dharam%20Singh%20became%20chief%20minister%20of%20Karnataka.%20Within%2021%20months%2C%20though%2C%20the%20JD(S)%20pulled%20out%20its%20support%20and%20the%20Dharam%20Singh%20government%20collapsed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumaraswamy%20shifted%20his%20support%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20became%20chief%20minister%20of%20Karnataka%20with%20the%20help%20of%20B.S.%20Yediyurappa%20in%20a%20power%20sharing%20agreement%2C%20according%20to%20which%20Kumaraswamy%20would%20be%20chief%20minister%20for%20the%20first%2020%20months%20followed%20by%20Yediyurappa%20for%20the%20remaining%2020%20months.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkarnataka-democracy-modi-shah%5C%22%3ETen%20Factors%20to%20Remember%20Amidst%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Win%20and%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Defeat%20in%20Karnataka%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYediyurappa%20became%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20as%20well%20as%20finance%20minister%20in%20Kumaraswamy%E2%80%99s%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20after%2020%20months%2C%20Kumaraswamy%20refused%20to%20relinquish%20his%20post.%20Deve%20Gowda%20and%20the%20JD(S)%20also%20supported%20his%20decision.%20He%20did%20resign%20some%20days%20later%20and%20Yediyurappa%20was%20made%20chief%20minister%20on%20November%2012%2C%202007.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20Kumaraswamy%20again%20withdrew%20his%20support%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20collapse%20within%20a%20week%20of%20its%20formation.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20BJP%20came%20close%20to%20forming%20a%20government%20in%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarly%20elections%20were%20called%20in%202008%20and%20Yediyurappa%2C%20riding%20the%20sympathy%20wave%20of%20the%20CM%E2%80%99s%20post%20being%20snatched%20away%20from%20him%2C%20made%20a%20big%20comeback%20and%20emerged%20as%20chief%20minister%20and%20a%20powerful%20Lingayat%20leader.%20It%20was%20a%20historical%20victory%20for%20the%20BJP%20under%20Yediyurappa%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20and%20the%20party%20made%20its%20entry%20in%20South%20India%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20similar%20situation%20occurred%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20election%20in%20the%20state%2C%20where%20no%20party%20won%20a%20majority.%20The%20Congress%20and%20the%20JD(S)%20formed%20a%20post-poll%20alliance%20and%20earned%20a%20majority%2C%20following%20which%20Kumaraswamy%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20chief%20minister%20for%20the%20second%20time.%20After%20one%20year%2C%20his%20government%20lost%20its%20majority%20when%2013%20MLAs%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20three%20MLAs%20of%20the%20JD(S)%20resigned%20in%20%E2%80%9COperation%20Lotus%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BJP%20then%20formed%20a%20government%20with%20Yediyurappa%20at%20its%20helm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20demise%20of%20the%20Janata%20Party%3A%20From%20alternative%20politics%20to%20question%20of%20existence%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202006%2C%20when%20Kumaraswamy%20formed%20the%20government%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20famous%20Kannada%20writer%20Dr%20U.R.%20Ananthamurthy%20had%20questioned%20the%20JD(S)%E2%80%99s%20secular%20credentials.%20Kumaraswamy%20had%20famously%20asked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2FU.R.-Ananthamurthy-controversies-in-political-cultural-arena%2Farticle60343404.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%20Dr%20Ananthamurthy%20was%20and%20what%20secularism%20meant%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20dilly-dallying%20on%20secularism%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20Kumaraswamy.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20characteristic%20of%20parties%20associated%20with%20the%20Janata%20Party.%20The%20Janata%20Party%20was%20formed%20in%201977%20to%20oppose%20the%20Emergency%20imposed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20with%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20(which%20later%20formed%20the%20BJP)%20as%20one%20of%20its%20significant%20constituent%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Janata%20Party%20came%20to%20power%20in%20seven%20states%2C%20namely%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%20But%20over%20the%20years%2C%20opportunism%2C%20a%20weak%20secular%20rhetoric%2C%20family-centred%20politics%20and%20over-reliance%20on%20specific%20caste%20groups%20have%20led%20to%20the%20slow%20demise%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%9Calternative%20politics%E2%80%9D%20symbolised%20by%20the%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-rahul-gandhi-1977-2004-election%5C%22%3EThose%20Who%20Write%20Off%20the%20Opposition%20Must%20Not%20Forget%20the%20Electoral%20Surprises%20of%201977%20and%202004%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20of%20the%20constituent%20parties%20and%20their%20leaders%20later%20aligned%20with%20the%20BJP%20to%20form%20coalition%20governments%20over%20the%20years%20and%20apparently%20had%20no%20problem%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20communal%20rhetoric%2C%20with%20Ram%20Vilas%20Paswan%20being%20a%20prime%20example%20of%20such%20a%20politics.%20He%20was%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20weatherman%20of%20Indian%20politics%20due%20to%20his%20flip-flops%20from%20one%20alliance%20to%20another%20to%20be%20in%20power%20or%20a%20ministership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENitish%20Kumar%20of%20the%20JD(U)%2C%20who%20had%20a%20strong%20base%20among%20Muslims%20in%20Bihar%20and%20had%20kept%20the%20state%20from%20the%20BJPs%E2%80%99%20clutches%2C%20has%20also%20succumbed%20to%20pressures%20from%20the%20BJP-driven%20ED%20and%20CBI%20raids.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20another%20reminder%20that%20such%20a%20polity%20might%20keep%20one%20in%20power%2C%20but%20with%20no%20teeth.%20Such%20alliances%20only%20weaken%20the%20regional%20party%E2%80%99s%20strength%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20national%20ambitions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20managed%20to%20snuff%20out%20many%20regional%20parties%2C%20either%20with%20ED%20raids%20or%20impotent%20alliances.%20Ineffective%20regional%20or%20third%20parties%20will%20help%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20idea%20of%20a%20two-party%20system%20that%20eventually%20benefits%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20ironic%20that%20members%20of%20the%20Janata%20Parivar%2C%20which%20was%20formed%20to%20oppose%20the%20authoritarianism%20of%20the%20Emergency%20era%2C%20are%20now%20happy%20bedfellows%20with%20the%20fascist%20forces%20in%20power.%20From%20playing%20a%20supportive%20role%20to%20fighting%20for%20survival%2C%20the%20kingmaker%20has%20met%20its%20fate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESwati%20Krishna%20is%20an%20activist%20and%20political%20observer%20based%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704213720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02200036%2FHDK.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fchanging-colours-of-h-d-kumaraswamy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kumaraswamy's%20mind%20seems%20to%20take%20a%20U-turn%20once%20every%20few%20years%2C%20especially%20when%20elections%20are%20around%20the%20corner.%20His%20changing%20stance%20is%20known%20in%20political%20circles%20and%20he%20is%20euphemistically%20called%20%E2%80%9Ckingmaker%E2%80%9D%20during%20every%20election%20in%20Karnataka.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fchanging-colours-of-h-d-kumaraswamy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Veggies%20dearer%2C%20petrol%20pumps%20run%20dry%20across%20India%20amid%20truckers'%20strike%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704213168000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2017-10%2F09%2Ffull%2F1507565604-6784.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fveggies-dearer-petrol-pumps-run-dry-across-india-amid-truckers-strike-124010201012_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Centre%20holding%20high-level%20meeting%20to%20break%20the%20impasse%20on%20Bharat%20Nyay%20Sanhita%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin