in%20case%20of%20any%20eventuality%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20ED%20summonses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElections%20to%20the%2081-member%20Jharkhand%20Assembly%20are%20due%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20JMM-led%20coalition%20has%20convened%20a%20meeting%20of%20its%20legislators%20here%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20discuss%20the%20present%20political%20situation%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704205680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Flp6bb04o_hemant-soren-_625x300_02_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpossibility-of-wife-contesting-polls-is-bjp-s-imagination-jkhand-cm-hemant-soren-4787527%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jharkhand%20Chief%20Minister%20Hemant%20Soren%20on%20Tuesday%20dismissed%20speculations%20of%20his%20wife%20Kalpana%20Soren%20contesting%20from%20Gandey%20assembly%20constituency%20in%20the%20state%20and%20termed%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20imagination%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20BJP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpossibility-of-wife-contesting-polls-is-bjp-s-imagination-jkhand-cm-hemant-soren-4787527%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpossibility-of-wife-contesting-polls-is-bjp-s-imagination-jkhand-cm-hemant-soren-4787527%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpossibility-of-wife-contesting-polls-is-bjp-s-imagination-jkhand-cm-hemant-soren-4787527%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20After%20Pivotal%202023%2C%20India%20Boldly%20Steps%20Into%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20strode%20prominently%20on%20the%20international%20stage%20in%202023.%20It%20chaired%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20as%20also%20the%20SCO%20summit%20(virtually).%20It%20attended%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20South%20Africa.%20India%20was%20invited%20to%20the%20G7%20summit%20in%20Japan%20where%20it%20also%20participated%20in%20the%20Quad%20meet.%20In%20organising%20a%20Voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20summit%20just%20before%20G20%2C%20India%20increased%20the%20diplomatic%20heft%20of%20its%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20bilateral%20level%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20as%20a%20special%20gesture%2C%20invited%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20the%20US%20on%20a%20state%20visit%2C%20which%20included%20an%20address%20to%20the%20US%20Congress.%20This%20wooing%20of%20India%20carried%20a%20significant%20political%20message%20about%20the%20growing%20strategic%20underpinnings%20of%20India-US%20ties%2C%20despite%20differences%20over%20our%20relations%20with%20Russia%2C%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20our%20refusal%20to%20impose%20sanctions%20on%20Moscow%2C%20and%20the%20campaign%20in%20US%20think%20tanks%2C%20media%2C%20academia%2C%20and%20human%20rights%20organisations%20against%20%26quot%3Bdemocracy%20backsliding%26quot%3B%20in%20India.%20US%20accusations%20of%20India's%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%20Pannun%20affair%20has%20been%20a%20troubling%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20invited%20Modi%20to%20the%20Bastille%20Day%20on%20July%2014%20as%20the%20Chief%20Guest%2C%20a%20gesture%20of%20high%20regard%20for%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20personally%20as%20well%20as%20a%20signal%20of%20the%20growing%20strategic%20understandings%20between%20France%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20developments%20had%20India's%20steady%20economic%20rise%2C%20its%20growing%20technological%20and%20human%20capacities%2C%20strong%2C%20purposeful%20and%20ambitious%20leadership%2C%20diplomatic%20dynamism%2C%20and%20an%20independent%20foreign%20policy%20as%20the%20backdrop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20of%20India's%20G20%20presidency%20was%20a%20tour%20de%20force%20in%20some%20ways.%20Without%20a%20Leaders'%20Declaration%20India%20would%20have%20suffered%20a%20serious%20diplomatic%20setback%20because%20of%20the%20massive%20political%20investment%20Modi%20had%20personally%20made%20in%20making%20the%20event%20emblematic%20of%20India's%20domestic%20and%20international%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20a%20declaration%20would%20have%20also%20put%20the%20G20%20in%20jeopardy%20as%20a%20platform%2C%20and%20this%20on%20India's%20watch%20would%20have%20been%20a%20blow%20to%20its%20rising%20profile.%20The%20opposition%20in%20India%20would%20have%20exploited%20any%20failure%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20national%20elections%20in%202024.%20India%2C%20however%2C%20was%20able%20to%20finalise%20a%20fully%20agreed%20Leader's%20Declaration%20without%20caveats%20by%20any%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20this%20proved%20possible%20despite%20the%20collapse%20of%20G7%20ties%20with%20Russia%20over%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20the%20draconian%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20by%20the%20West%20that%20inflicted%20serious%20economic%20costs%20on%20the%20Global%20South%20by%20way%20of%20food%2C%20fertiliser%20shortages%20and%20disruptions%20in%20energy%20flows%2C%20was%20remarkable.%20The%20final%20declaration%20carries%20a%20substantial%20paragraph%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20met%20the%20diplomatic%20needs%20of%20both%20the%20G7%20and%20Russia%20backed%20by%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20openly%20adversarial%20relationship%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20has%20disrupted%20international%20politics%20as%20well%20as%20existing%20economic%20and%20technology%20frameworks%2C%20led%20to%20moves%20to%20restructure%20global%20supply%20chains%20and%20raised%20the%20spectre%20of%20a%20conflict%20in%20the%20western%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20now%20openly%20challenging%20US%20power.%20Through%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI)%2C%20it%20has%20knit%20relations%20with%20all%20corners%20of%20the%20globe%20in%20trade%2C%20control%20of%20vital%20raw%20materials%20and%20infrastructure%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20West-built%20international%20order%20is%20being%20eroded%2C%20with%20Russia%20and%20China%20seeking%20to%20actively%20promote%20a%20multi-polar%20order.%20The%20Global%20South%20as%20well%20as%20some%20non-western%20countries%20hitherto%20politically%20and%20militarily%20dependent%20on%20the%20US%20are%20now%20pursuing%20hedging%20strategies%20and%20striving%20to%20balance%20their%20external%20ties%20by%20reaching%20out%20to%20China%2C%20even%20to%20the%20point%20of%20seeking%20its%20good%20offices%20to%20bring%20about%20reconciliation%20between%20regional%20adversaries%2C%20in%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20West%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20has%20consequences%20for%20multilateralism%20and%20collectively%20addressing%20pressing%20issues%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20issues%20of%20financial%20and%20technology%20transfers%20to%20developing%20countries%20and%20energy%20transition.%20(India%20stood%20its%20ground%20on%20its%20core%20interests%20at%20the%20Cop%2028%20summit%20at%20Dubai%20in%20November%2FDecember%202023).%20The%20indebtedness%20of%20developing%20countries%2C%20the%20accelerated%20implementation%20of%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20needs%20genuine%20global%20cooperation%2C%20which%20will%20be%20impeded%20by%20the%20fractures%20in%20the%20international%20system.%20On%20top%20of%20this%2C%20India%20and%20China%20are%20locked%20in%20a%20military%20confrontation%20in%20the%20Himalayas%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20east.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20broad%20international%20context%20that%20India's%20G20%20success%20in%20developing%20a%20consensus%20on%20all%20vital%20issues%20facing%20the%20international%20community%20and%20bridging%20the%20divides%20should%20be%20assessed.%20India%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20consensus-builder%20and%20a%20proponent%20of%20dialogue%20and%20diplomacy%20to%20resolve%20differences.%20It%20has%20credibility%20with%20both%20the%20North%20and%20the%20South%2C%20and%20to%20some%20degree%20the%20West%20and%20East%20(China%20apart).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20capitalised%20on%20its%20policy%20of%20engaging%20all%2C%20even%20those%20who%20are%20mutual%20adversaries.%20Its%20membership%20of%20BRICS%20and%20SCO%20while%20as%20it%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Quad%20supports%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20concept.%20India%20has%20grown%20visibly%20closer%20to%20the%20US%20even%20in%20the%20defence%20domain%2C%20which%20has%20given%20the%20country%20more%20room%20to%20manoeuvre%20on%20the%20international%20stage%2C%20and%20made%20it%20a%20valued%20partner%20to%20those%20who%20want%20to%20preserve%20the%20present%20%26quot%3Binternational%20order%26quot%3B%20as%20also%20those%20who%20want%20to%20reform%20it%20or%20even%20challenge%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20projecting%20itself%20as%20an%20upholder%20of%20the%20international%20order%2C%20albeit%20a%20reformed%20and%20a%20more%20democratic%20and%20equitable%20one.%20It%20sees%20building%20closer%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20as%20necessary%20for%20trade%20and%20access%20to%20capital.%20Cooperation%20in%20advanced%20technologies%20with%20the%20US%20is%20considered%20critical%20for%20India's%20economic%20growth%20and%20competitiveness.%20India%20wants%20to%20be%20a%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20shift%20in%20global%20supply%20chains%20hitherto%20concentrated%20in%20one%20geography.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20seeks%20a%20greater%20voice%20and%20role%20for%20itself%20and%20for%20the%20developing%20world%20in%20international%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20summit%20in%20January%202023%20was%20intended%20to%20shift%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20G20%20from%20G%207%20priorities%20to%20those%20of%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20such%20as%20managing%20global%20debt%20vulnerabilities%2C%20food%20and%20energy%20security%2C%20eliminating%20hunger%2C%20climate%20change%20financing%2C%20affordable%2C%20just%20and%20sustainable%20green%20development%2C%20focus%20on%20SDGs%2C%20reforming%20international%20financial%20institutions%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Promoting%20the%20G20%20membership%20of%20the%20African%20Union%20was%20part%20of%20this%20strategy.%20India%20convened%20the%20second%20summit%20of%20the%20Voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20November%202023%20to%20maintain%20the%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20membership%20of%20BRICS%20meets%20the%20goal%20of%20%26quot%3Binternational%20re-balancing%26quot%3B%2C%20though%20the%20expansion%20process%20is%20not%20based%20on%20any%20clear%20criteria%20and%20is%20being%20thrust%20forward%20by%20China%20and%20Russia%20as%20part%20of%20their%20push%20for%20%26quot%3Bmultipolarity%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20is%20a%20code%20word%20for%20countering%20the%20US%20dominance%20of%20the%20global%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SCO%20summit%20India%20chaired%20in%20July%2C%20although%20a%20platform%20for%20cooperation%20in%20Central%20Asia%20that%20excludes%20the%20West%2C%20has%2C%20for%20New%20Delhi%2C%20a%20logic%20beyond%20that.%20India%20as%20an%20Asian%20power%20cannot%20allow%20itself%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20the%20Asian%20landmass%20and%20must%20remain%20a%20balancing%20factor%20in%20the%20power%20equations%20in%20this%20region%2C%20which%20are%20moving%20in%20China's%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20Delhi%20SCO%20Declaration%20emphasised%20greater%20effectiveness%20of%20global%20institutions%3B%20a%20more%20representative%2C%20democratic%2C%20just%20and%20multipolar%20world%20order%20based%20on%20international%20law%3B%20multilateralism%3B%20equal%2C%20joint%2C%20indivisible%2C%20comprehensive%20and%20sustainable%20security%3B%20and%20cultural%20and%20civilizational%20diversity%2C%20with%20a%20central%20coordinating%20role%20of%20the%20UN.%20It%20stressed%20that%20unilateral%20application%20of%20economic%20sanctions%20other%20than%20those%20approved%20by%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20was%20incompatible%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20international%20law%20and%20had%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20the%20third%20world%20countries%20and%20international%20economic%20relations.%20All%20this%20reflects%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20West%20dominated%20global%20system%20and%20the%20need%20for%20change%20and%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20President%20Biden%20unable%20to%20attend%20India's%20Republic%20Day%20in%202024%2C%20and%20the%20consequent%20postponement%20of%20the%20Quad%20summit%2C%20President%20Macron's%20willingness%20to%20step%20in%20shows%20both%20the%20personal%20chemistry%20between%20him%20and%20Modi%20and%20the%20deepening%20strategic%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%20This%20was%20already%20reflected%20in%20Macron's%20invite%20to%20Modi%20to%20be%20chief%20guest%20at%20Bastille%20Day%20on%20July%2014%2C%20when%20the%20two%20sides%20laid%20the%20foundations%20of%20a%20strategic%20relationship%20spanning%20the%20next%2025%20years%20by%20adopting%20the%20%26quot%3BHorizon%202047%20Roadmap%20on%20the%2025th%20Anniversary%20of%20the%20Indo-French%20Strategic%20Partnership%3A%20towards%20a%20century%20of%20French-Indian%20relations%26quot%3B.%20India%20and%20France%20adopted%20a%20new%20Indo-Pacific%20Roadmap%20during%20Modi's%20visit%2C%20which%20includes%20extending%20their%20cooperation%20to%20the%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202023%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20invited%20to%20the%20G7%20summit%20in%20Japan%2C%20also%20attended%20the%20Quad%20summit.%20In%20his%20opening%20statement%2C%20Modi%20spelt%20out%20the%20importance%20India%20now%20attaches%20to%20the%20Quad%2C%20both%20on%20the%20security%20and%20economic%20fronts.%20He%20spoke%20of%20the%20Quad%20establishing%20itself%20as%20an%20important%20platform%20for%20ensuring%20peace%2C%20stability%20and%20prosperity%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20recognised%20that%20the%20security%20and%20success%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20was%20important%20also%20to%20the%20world.%20Modi%20reiterated%20that%20India%20now%20saw%20Quad%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20good%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20Hiroshima%2C%20India%20joined%20the%20vigorous%20criticism%20of%20China's%20policies%20in%20the%20western%20Pacific%20that%20adversely%20affect%20India's%20interests%20too.%20India-China%20ties%20remain%20frozen%20at%20the%20political%20level.%20China%20has%20not%20appointed%20an%20ambassador%20to%20India%20since%20October%202022.%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20meeting%20of%20India's%20Foreign%20Minister%20with%20his%20Chinese%20counterpart%20in%20Delhi%20during%20the%20SCO%20Foreign%20Ministers'%20meeting%20produced%20no%20change%20in%20positions.%20China%20is%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20will%20not%20make%20any%20concessions%20on%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%2C%20and%20that%20India%20must%20accept%20the%20new%20realities%20on%20the%20ground.%20India%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20reiterated%20several%20times%20in%202023%20that%20for%20ties%20to%20be%20normal%2C%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20border%20has%20to%20become%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20Jaishankar's%20five-day%20visit%20to%20Russia%20in%20late%20December%20was%20politically%20necessary%20in%20the%20absence%2C%20again%2C%20last%20year%20of%20an%20India-Russia%20summit.%20Any%20feeling%20that%20the%20relationship%20was%20losing%20its%20vitality%20needed%20countering.%20Jaishankar's%20visit%20sent%20a%20clear%20political%20message%20-%20India%20will%20continue%20to%20nurture%20its%20ties%20with%20Russia%2C%20undeterred%20by%20pressures%20by%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20was%20received%20by%20Putin%20who%20does%20not%20usually%20meet%20Foreign%20Ministers.%20Putin%20has%20in%20fact%20been%20publicly%20praising%20Modi%20for%20refusing%20to%20be%20intimidated%20and%20for%20pursuing%20India's%20national%20interest%20despite%20pressures.%20Jaishankar%20delivered%20a%20personal%20message%20from%20Modi%20to%20Putin%2C%20who%2C%20during%20the%20meeting%2C%20invited%20his%20%26quot%3Bfriend%20Modi%26quot%3B%20to%20visit%20Russia%20in%202024%2C%20a%20prospective%20Jaishankar%20endorsed.%20Jaishankar%20noted%20that%20after%20talks%20with%20Sergey%20Lavrov%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20clearly%20came%20out%20was%20that%20India-Russia%20relations%20remain%20very%20steady%2C%20remain%20very%20strong%2C%20they%20are%20based%20on%20our%20strategic%20convergence%2C%20on%20our%20geopolitical%20interests%2C%20and%20because%20they%20are%20mutually%20beneficial%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20India%20steps%20into%202024%20with%20greater%20self-confidence%20and%20a%20higher%20international%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704205560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F5d3kch0o_pm-modi-tamil-nadu_625x300_02_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fafter-pivotal-2023-india-boldly-steps-into-2024-4787523%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20strode%20prominently%20on%20the%20international%20stage%20in%202023.%20It%20chaired%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20as%20also%20the%20SCO%20summit%20(virtually).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fafter-pivotal-2023-india-boldly-steps-into-2024-4787523%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.nd