th%20the%20freedom%20of%20peaceful%20assembly%20and%20freedom%20of%20association%3B%20restrictions%20on%20freedom%20of%20movement%20and%20on%20the%20right%20to%20leave%20the%20country%3B%20refoulement%20of%20refugees%3B%20serious%20government%20corruption%3B%20harassment%20of%20domestic%20and%20international%20human%20rights%20organizations%E2%80%9D%3B%C2%A0%20(and)%20%E2%80%9Ccrimes%20involving%20violence%20or%20threats%20of%20violence%20targeting%20members%20of%20national%2Fracial%2Fethnic%20and%20minority%20groups%20based%20on%20religious%20affiliation%2C%20social%20status%20or%20sexual%20orientation%E2%80%A6A%20lack%20of%20accountability%20for%20official%20misconduct%20persisted%20at%20all%20levels%20of%20government%2C%20contributing%20to%20widespread%20impunity.%20%E2%80%A6Lax%20enforcement%2C%20a%20shortage%20of%20trained%20police%20officers%2C%20and%20an%20overburdened%20and%20under%20resourced%20court%20system%20contributed%20to%20a%20low%20number%20of%20convictions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20where%20the%20BJP%20had%20already%20taken%20India%20in%20the%20esteem%20of%20the%20world%2C%20before%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20plans%20to%20assassinate%20prominent%20Khalistanis%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20were%20exposed%20by%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Five%20Eyes%E2%80%99%20intelligence%20consortium.%20But%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Mahua%20Moitra%20from%20Parliament%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20report%20by%20an%20Ethics%20Committee%20from%20which%20the%20entire%20opposition%20had%20walked%20out%20in%20protest%20against%20the%20demeaning%2C%20sexual%20innuendo-loaded%20questions%20that%20its%20chairman%2C%20Vinod%20Kumar%20Sonkar%20%2Cwas%20asking%2C%20reeks%20of%20a%20sexual%20misogyny%20that%20has%20brought%20shame%20upon%20our%20parliament%20and%20country%20across%20the%20entire%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20accused%20Moitra%20of%20almost%20everything%20it%20could%C2%A0%20think%20of.%20Chief%20among%20the%20grounds%20given%20for%20her%20expulsion%20is%20her%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Chighly%20objectionable%2C%20unethical%2C%20heinous%20and%20criminal%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20before%20the%20committee.%20But%C2%A0%20even%20a%20cursory%20examination%20of%20the%20record%20of%20its%20meetings%20shows%20that%20Moitra%20treated%20the%20committee%20with%20respect%2C%C2%A0%20and%20answered%20every%20question%20relating%20to%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20her%20detractors%20fully.%20In%20her%20replies%2C%20which%20occupy%2016%20long%20paragraphs%20spread%20over%20pages%2032%20till%2040%2C%20she%20remained%20deferential%20and%20gave%20detailed%20explanations%20of%20her%20actions%20throughout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20kernel%20of%20the%20charge%20Moitra%20faced%20was%20that%20she%20had%20given%20her%20login%20and%20password%20to%20an%20unauthorised%20person%2C%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20and%20allowed%20him%20to%20send%20in%20questions%20in%20her%20name%20that%20were%20designed%20to%20damage%20the%20reputation%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20government.%20By%20doing%20this%20she%20had%20breached%20confidentiality%20and%20endangered%20national%20security.%20What%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20explain%20was%20how%20anyone%20could%20have%20uploaded%20a%20question%20in%20her%20name%20without%20sending%20an%20OTP%2C%20as%20is%20required%20in%20India%20by%20all%20online%20business%20transactions%2C%20and%20is%20mandatory%20for%20MPs%20filing%20questions%20in%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Did%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Follow%20Due%20Process%20While%20Expelling%20Mahua%20Moitra%20From%20the%20House%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdid-the-lok-sabha-follow-due-process-while-expelling-mahua-moitra-from-the-house%5C%22%3EDid%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Follow%20Due%20Process%20While%20Expelling%20Mahua%20Moitra%20From%20the%20House%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20OTP%20had%20to%20come%20from%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20phone%2C%20and%20so%20any%20verification%20would%20necessitate%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20involement.%20So%20no%20matter%20who%20had%20given%20Moitra%20the%20information%20upon%20which%20she%20based%20a%20question%20in%20parliament%2C%20and%20who%20typed%20and%20mailed%20it%20for%20her%2C%20once%20she%20had%20sent%20the%20OTP%2C%20%3Cem%3Eit%20became%20her%20question.%3C%2Fem%3E%20If%20she%20sent%20the%20question%20to%20Hiranandani%2C%20which%20the%20records%20show%20she%20undoubtedly%20did%2C%20it%20would%20not%20only%20have%20been%20to%20get%20it%20typed%2C%20which%20is%20admittedly%20a%20not%20very%20credible%20reason%2C%20but%20for%20verification%20of%20the%20facts%20that%20she%20was%20citing.%20That%20is%20something%20every%20responsible%20journalist%C2%A0%20does%2C%20so%20why%20should%20a%20member%20of%20parliament%20not%20do%20so%20in%C2%A0%20matters%20of%20infinitely%20greater%20importance%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%20even%20her%20explanation%20that%20she%20had%20sent%20her%20parliamentary%20questions%20to%20Hiranandani%E2%80%99s%20office%20only%20for%20typing%20and%20uploading%20on%20the%20net%20because%20these%20can%20no%20longer%20be%20submitted%20in%20handwritten%20form%2C%20was%20not%20a%20subterfuge.%20For%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20had%20confirmed%20to%20the%20committee%20that%20all%20of%20her%2061%20questions%2C%20of%20which%2090%25%20had%20little%20or%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20Hiranandani%20enterprises%2C%20had%20also%20been%20posted%20from%20his%20Dubai%20IP%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20when%20the%20committee%20chairman%2C%20Sonkar%20asked%20her%20five%20questions%20that%2C%20taken%20together%2C%20insinuated%20that%20she%20was%20loose%20woman%20having%20an%20affair%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20and%20was%20giving%20him%20sexual%20favours%20for%20information%20with%20which%20to%20attack%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20that%20she%20stormed%20out.%20The%20questions%20were%3A%20i)%20What%20is%20your%20relationship%20with%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%3F%20ii)%20How%20many%20times%20did%20you%20visit%20Dubai%3F%20(iii)%20Where%20did%20you%20stay%20iv)%20in%20which%20hotel%3B%20v)%20%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20meet%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20there%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20was%20the%20fifth%20question%20that%20made%20her%20lose%20her%20temper%20and%20storm%20out.%20Every%20self-respecting%20woman%2C%20whether%20an%20MP%20or%20not%2C%20would%20have%20done%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sonkar%20asked%20these%20questions%2C%20the%20committee%20had%20already%20been%C2%A0%20informed%20that%20Moitra%20had%20visited%20Dubai%20only%20four%20times%20in%20nearly%20five%20years%20%E2%80%93%20hardly%20often%20enough%20to%20sustain%20a%20clandestine%20affair%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20the%20timing%20of%20her%20visits%20was%20not%20even%20remotely%20connected%20with%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20questions%20she%20had%20posed%20to%20the%20petroleum%20and%20natural%20gas%20ministry.%20Moitra%20did%20not%20know%20this%2C%20so%20she%20had%20responded%20to%20the%20accusation%2C%20indirectly%20supported%20by%20Hiranandani%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%2C%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20her%20being%20able%20to%20%3Cem%3Eforce%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20dollar%20trillionaire%20with%20a%20vast%20international%20construction%20company%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Unicorn%20%E2%80%93%20to%20do%20anything%20illegal%20was%20ludicrous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Sonkar%20ignored%20all%20this%20and%20deliberately%20asked%20her%20questions%20that%20invaded%20her%20privacy%2C%20and%20would%20have%20been%20resented%20by%20any%20self-respecting%20woman%2C%20and%20drove%20her%20into%20losing%20her%20temper%20and%20storming%20out.%20Sonkar%20succeeded%2C%20knowing%20that%20this%20would%20make%20any%20further%20inquiry%20into%20her%20actions%20before%20recommending%20her%20expulsion%20superfluous.%20He%20will%20no%20doubt%20be%20rewarded%20in%20due%20course%20as%20Anurag%20Thakur%20and%20Kapil%20Mishra%20were%20rewarded%20after%20the%20police%20firing%20upon%20Shaheen%20Bagh%20protestors%20and%20the%20North-East%20Delhi%20communal%20violence%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20question%20no%20one%20has%20asked%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%20question%20no%20one%20has%20asked%20is%2C%20what%20was%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20tearing%20need%20for%20hurry%20that%20made%20the%20government%20target%20and%20destroy%20Mahua%20Moitra%20%3Cem%3Enow%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20So%20great%20was%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20hurry%20that%20it%20could%20not%20give%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20even%20a%20day%20to%20read%20its%20495%20page%20report%2C%20took%20less%20than%2030%20minutes%20after%20Moitra%20stormed%20out%20of%20the%20final%20hearing%20to%20recommend%20her%20expulsion%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20and%20carried%20this%20out%20the%20very%20next%20day%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20almost%20certainly%20lies%20buried%20in%20the%20ongoing%20rapid%20privatisation%20of%20port%20and%20LNG%20terminal%20development%20that%20has%20taken%20place%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministership.%20This%20began%20in%202018%2C%20and%20has%20gathered%20momentum%20rapidly%20since%20then.%20The%20principal%2C%20but%20not%20only%2C%C2%A0%20beneficiary%20of%20this%20shift%20from%20reliance%20on%20the%20public%20sector%20has%20been%20the%20Adani%20group%20of%20enterprises.%20A%20second%20major%20player%20has%20been%20H-Energy%2C%20an%20increasingly%20important%20part%20of%20the%20Hiranandani%20group.%20In%20Bengal%2C%20the%20competition%20between%20these%20groups%20was%20won%20by%20the%20Hiranandani%20group.%20In%20Odisha%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20it%20is%20being%20won%20mostly%20by%20the%20Adani%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%209%2C%202019%2C%20H-Energy%2C%20the%20energy%20arm%20of%20the%20Hiranandani%20group%2C%20entered%20into%20negotiations%20with%C2%A0%20the%20Calcutta%20Port%20Trust%20to%20set%20up%20an%20initially%20three%2C%20and%20eventually%20five%2C%20million%20tonnes%20a%20year%20Liquefied%20Natural%20Gas%20(LNG)%20terminal%20at%20Kukrahati%2C%20near%20Haldia%20port.%20These%20negotiations%20were%20completed%20in%20February%202021%2C%20when%20the%20Kolkata%20Port%20Trust%20signed%20an%20agreement%20with%20it%20for%20a%20project%20involving%20an%20investment%20of%20Rs%203%2C900%20core%2C%20which%20would%20yield%20gross%20revenues%20of%20around%20Rs%206%2C000%20crore.%20The%20construction%20of%20the%20terminal%20has%20been%20delayed%20because%20the%20group%20proposes%20to%20use%20Kukrahati%20for%20supplying%20LNG%20to%20Bangladesh%20as%20well%2C%20and%20is%20building%20a%20150%20km%20pipeline%20for%20this.%20It%20is%20now%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20by%20the%20middle%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20only%20one%20of%20several%20port%20and%20gas%20terminal%20projects%20being%20planned%20and%20executed%20along%20the%20east%20and%20west%20coasts.%20H-Energy%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20partnering%20with%20Jindal%20Steel%20Works%20to%20build%20an%20LNG%20terminal%20at%20Jaygarh%2C%20in%20Maharashtra.%20Essar%20has%20won%20a%20contract%20to%20build%20a%20one%20million%20tonnes%20per%20year%20LNG%20facility%20at%20Haldia%20port.%20But%20the%20biggest%20player%20in%20this%20is%20the%20Adani%20Group%2C%20which%20is%20building%20a%20giant%20facility%20at%20Dhamra%20port%20in%20Odisha%2C%20and%20actively%20bidding%20for%20more%20contracts%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Bengal%20and%20on%20the%20west%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbsent%20from%20this%20hectic%20activity%20is%20Petronet%2C%20the%20public%20sector%20consortium%20consisting%20of%20the%20Gas%20Authority%20of%20India%20Ltd%20(GAIL)%2C%20Oil%20and%20Natural%20Gas%20Corporation%20(ONGC)%2C%20Indian%20Oil%20Corporation%20(IOCL)%20and%20Bharat%20Petroleum%20(BPCL)%2C%20that%20set%20up%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20giant%20LNG%20receiving%20and%20regasification%20terminal%20at%20Dahej%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20with%C2%A0%20a%20nominal%20capacity%20of%2017.5%20MMTPA%20(million%20metric%20tonnes%20per%20annum)%2C%20and%20another%20terminal%20at%20Kochi%2C%20Kerala%20with%20a%20capacity%20of%20five%20MMTPA.%20Petronet%E2%80%99s%20terminals%20account%20for%20around%2040%25%20gas%20supplies%20in%20the%20country%20and%20handle%20around%20two-thirds%20of%20its%20LNG%20imports.%20But%20today%20it%20is%20nowhere%20in%20the%20scene%2C%20and%20is%20at%20most%20a%20minor%20shareholder%20in%20a%20few%20of%20the%20projects%20that%20are%20coming%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20of%20emphasis%20has%20taken%20pace%20entirely%20during%20the%20Modi%20era.%20So%20it%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20five%20out%20of%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%2091%20questions%20have%20asked%20for%20details%20concerning%20the%20way%20it%20has%20been%20made.%20In%20these%20she%20has%20questioned%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20how%20the%20Dhamra%20port%20LNG%20terminal%20project%2C%20which%20began%20as%20a%20proposal%20by%20GAIL%20and%20ONGC%2C%20became%20a%20wholly%20owned%20Adani%20enterprise.%20These%20questions%20were%20posed%20on%20July%208%2C%202019%2C%20November%2018%2C%202019%20and%20December%209%2C%202019.%20Then%2C%20after%20a%203.5%20year%20gap%20on%20March%2016%2C%202023%2C%20and%20then%20only%20a%20week%20later%20on%20March%2023%2C%202023.%20All%20of%20them%20centred%20around%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20public%20sector%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20were%20being%20pushed%2C%20or%20shut%2C%20out%20of%20existing%20and%20proposed%20projects%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20LNG%20terminals%20and%20other%20facilities%20at%20the%20ports%20being%20developed%20on%20the%20east%20and%20west%20coasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22(At%20Least)%20Three%20Critical%20Flaws%20in%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20Report%20on%20Mahua%20Moitra%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fat-least-three-critical-flaws-in-the-ethics-committee-report-on-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3E(At%20Least)%20Three%20Critical%20Flaws%20in%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20Report%20on%20Mahua%20Moitra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20contracts%20were%20ending%20up%20with%20the%20Adani%20group.%20Moitra%20wanted%20to%20know%20why.%20To%20get%20an%20answer%20from%20the%20government%2C%20she%20focused%20on%20the%20route%20by%20which%20the%20group%20gained%20full%20ownership%20of%20the%20LNG%20terminal%20planned%20for%20Dhamra%20port%20in%20Odisha.%20Her%20interest%20had%20been%20sparked%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20in%202013%2C%20i.e.%20during%20the%20UPA%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20GAIL%20had%20entered%20into%20a%20contract%20with%20the%20government%20of%20Odisha%20to%20build%20a%20floating%20LNG%20terminal%20at%20the%20port%20of%20Paradip%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%202%2C485%20crore.%20But%20in%202015%2C%20a%20year%20after%20the%20BJP%20came%20to%20power%2C%20it%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Paradip%20project%20and%20took%20an%2011%25%20share%20in%20a%20similar%20project%20at%20Dhamra%20port%2C%20also%20in%20Odisha.%20IOCL%2C%20another%20member%20of%20Petronet%2C%C2%A0%20took%2038%25.%20The%20other%2051%25%20was%20to%20be%20taken%20by%20%E2%80%98an%20unspecified%20partner%E2%80%99.%20That%20partner%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20Adani%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20only%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20shift.%20Another%20two%20years%20later%2C%20GAIL%20and%20IOCL%20both%20withdrew%20from%20the%20project%2C%20leaving%20the%20Adani%20group%20the%20sole%20owner.%20This%20company%20then%20signed%20a%2020-year%20contract%20to%20supply%20three%20million%20tonnes%20a%20year%20of%20LNG%20to%20GAIL%20and%20IOCL%20at%20Rs%2060.28%20per%20MMBtu%2C%20with%20an%20escalation%20clause%20of%205%25%20a%20year.%20This%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98use%20or%20pay%E2%80%99%20contract%2C%20in%20which%20the%20buyers%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20all%20of%20the%20contracted%20amount%20even%20if%20they%20did%20not%20lift%20it.%20Moitra%20claimed%20that%20with%20this%20assured%20return%2C%20Adani%20had%20no%20difficulty%20in%20roping%20in%20the%20French%20oil%20and%20gas%20giant%2C%20Total%2C%20as%20a%20partner.%20From%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20it%20was%20a%20good%20deal.%20But%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20was%20engineered%20was%20all%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20admitted%2C%20perhaps%20unwittingly%2C%20by%20advocate%20Jai%20Dehadrai%20(Moitra%E2%80%99s%20former%20lover)%20himself%20in%20the%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98Remarks%E2%80%99%20column%20that%20he%20had%20added%20to%20the%20list%20that%20he%20submitted%20to%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20of%20the%20questions%20that%C2%A0%20Moitra%20had%20posed%20in%20Parliament.%20In%20these%20he%20accused%20Moitra%20of%20targeting%20the%20prime%20minister%20by%20asking%20questions%20that%20were%20designed%20to%20show%20how%20his%20government%20was%20helping%20the%20Adani%20group%20to%20evade%20the%20tendering%20process%20and%C2%A0%20violate%20the%20guidelines%20set%20by%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20to%20acquire%20the%20Dhamra%20LNG%20project.%20This%20was%20being%20done%20by%20first%20getting%20state-owned%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20to%20tender%20for%20a%20project%2C%20and%20then%20making%20them%20withdraw%20in%20favour%20of%20Adani.%20This%2C%20she%20claimed%2C%20was%20a%20more%20sophisticated%20way%20of%20doing%20what%20his%20government%20had%20done%20earlier%2C%20to%20eject%C2%A0%20GVK%20from%20the%20Mumbai%20Airport%20modernisation%20project%20and%20hand%20it%20over%20to%20the%20Adani%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20determination%20to%20punish%20his%20ex%2C%20Dehedrai%20went%20a%20step%20further%20and%20accused%20Moitra%20of%20repeating%20these%20allegations%20in%20her%20March%2016%20unstarred%20question%20this%20year%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20solely%20in%20order%20to%20add%20to%20the%20discomfiture%20caused%20to%20the%20government%20by%20the%20Adani-Hindenburg%20exposures.%20In%20doing%20this%20he%20unwittingly%20gave%20the%20game%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2016%20this%20year%2C%20Moitra%20had%20posed%20the%20following%20seven-part%20question%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWill%20the%20Minister%20of%20Petroleum%20and%20Natural%20Gas%20be%20pleased%20to%20state%20(a)%20the%20details%C2%A0%20of%C2%A0%20Indian%C2%A0%20Oil%20Corporation%20Ltd.%20(IOCL)%20Memorandum%20of%20Undcrstanding%20(MoU)%20signed%20with%20Adani%20Ports%20and%20Special%20Economic%20Zone%20Limited%20at%20Gangavaram%20Port%20%2C%20duration%C2%A0%20of%20contract%2C%20take%20or%20pay%20commitments%20along%20with%20price%20and%20volume%20per%20annum%20and%20escalations%20in%20the%20contract%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(b)%20whether%20this%20MoU%20bas%20been%20approved%20by%20the%20Board%20of%20IOCL%20and%20if%20so.%20the%20details%20there%20of%C2%A0%20(c)%20whether%20there%20is%20any%20Government%20nominee%20on%20the%20Board%20of%20IOCL%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20details%20thereof%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(d)whether%20there%20is%20any%20transaction%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20approval%20has%20been%20taken%20for%20such%20transaction%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(e)whether%20it%20is%20true%20that%20IOCL%20would%20move%20its%20business%C2%A0from%20Vizag%20Port%20to%20Gangavaram%20Port%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20reasons%20thereof%20along%20with%20the%20charges%20paid%20to%20Vizag%20Port%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(f)%20whether%20there%20are%20any%20payment-related%20commitments%20at%20Vizag%20Port%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20details%20thereof%3B%20and%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(g)%20the%20details%20of%20the%20annual%20payments%20and%20quantities%20imported%20by%20IOCL%20to%20Vizag.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20mammoth%20query%20sealed%20her%20fate.%20For%20if%20the%20government%20answered%20it%2C%20the%20entire%20country%20would%20see%20that%20it%20was%20a%20repeat%20of%20what%20had%20happened%20at%20Dhamra.%20This%20would%20give%20the%20still-to-be-born%20INDIA%20alliance%20a%20golden%20opportunity%20to%20show%20the%20country%20how%20the%20Modi%20government%20was%20quietly%20breaking%20every%20rule%20and%20convention%20in%20order%20to%20find%20ways%20of%20handing%20over%20their%20future%20to%20a%20single%2C%20highly%20favoured%20industrial%20group%2C%20and%20to%20start%20asking%20what%20was%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoitra%20had%20therefore%20to%20be%20to%20be%20stopped%20from%20demanding%20an%20answer%20in%20parliament%2C%20which%20is%20now%20a%20televised%20forum%20that%20the%20whole%20country%20watches.%20The%20one%20way%20to%20do%20this%20was%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20expel%20her%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20It%20did%20this%20by%20exploiting%20a%20path%20that%20she%20herself%20had%20opened%2C%20by%20her%20behaviour%20as%20a%20single%2C%20highly%20educated%20and%20self-confident%20woman%20who%20could%20choose%20her%20friends%20and%20lovers%20%E2%80%93%20everything%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctraditional%E2%80%9D%20Indian%20women%20have%20been%20trained%2C%20or%20forced%2C%20to%20suppress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fprem-shankar-jha%5C%22%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Jha%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704198649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02161150%2FF8yrxWGb0AAOZ15.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-mahua-moitra-lng-adani%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20answer%20almost%20certainly%20lies%20buried%20in%20the%20ongoing%20rapid%20privatisation%20of%20port%20and%20LNG%20terminal%20development%20that%20has%20taken%20place%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministership.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A57%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-mahua-moitra-lng-adani%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Donkey%20Flight'%20Fliers%20From%20Gujarat%20Agreed%20To%20Pay%20Rs%2060%20Lakh%20To%20Enter%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2060%20people%20from%20Gujarat%20on%20board%20the%20Nicaragua-bound%20plane%2C%20which%20was%20sent%20back%20from%20France%20over%20suspected%20human%20trafficking%2C%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20Rs%2060%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2080%20lakh%20to%20immigration%20agents%2C%20who%20promised%20to%20cross%20into%20the%20US%20illegally%20after%20reaching%20the%20Latin%20American%20country%2C%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nicaragua-bound%20aircraft%2C%20an%20Airbus%20A340%20carrying%20303%20passengers%2C%20including%20260%20Indians%2C%20was%20grounded%20in%20France%20for%20four%20days%20over%20suspected%20human%20trafficking%20over%20a%20week%20ago.%20It%20landed%20in%20Mumbai%20in%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20December%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20senior%20state%20Crime%20Investigation%20Department%20(CID)%20-%20Crime%20and%20Railways%20official%2C%20those%20passengers%20included%2066%20from%20Gujarat%2C%20who%20have%20already%20reached%20their%20respective%20native%20places%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuperintendent%20of%20Police%2C%20CID-%20Crime%20and%20Railways%2C%20Sanjay%20Kharat%2C%20who%20is%20investigating%20the%20case%2C%20said%20these%2066%20Gujarat%20natives%2C%20including%20some%20minors%2C%20were%20mainly%20from%20Mehsana%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Gandhinagar%20and%20Anand%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20already%20questioned%2055%20of%20them%20and%20recorded%20their%20statements.%20Majority%20of%20them%20have%20studied%20till%20Class%208%20to%2012.%20Each%20of%20them%20admitted%20that%20they%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20Rs%2060%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2080%20lakh%20to%20the%20local%20immigration%20agents%20to%20help%20them%20cross%20into%20the%20US%20illegally%20after%20reaching%20Nicaragua%20via%20Dubai%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20CID%20has%20so%20far%20acquired%20the%20names%20and%20contact%20numbers%20of%20nearly%2015%20agents%2C%20who%20had%20promised%20to%20help%20these%2055%20persons%20enter%20the%20US%20illegally%20through%20the%20US-Mexico%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20agents%20had%20asked%20these%2055%20persons%20to%20pay%20the%20money%20only%20after%20reaching%20the%20US.%20The%20agents%20had%20told%20the%20passengers%20that%20their%20men%20would%20take%20them%20to%20the%20US%20border%20from%20Nicaragua%20and%20then%20help%20them%20cross%20the%20border.%20It%20was%20also%20revealed%20that%20the%20agents%20had%20also%20booked%20air%20tickets%20for%20these%20passengers%20and%20gave%20USD%201%2C000%20to%203%2C000%20to%20each%20passenger%20to%20deal%20with%20any%20emergency%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Kharat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20plan%20devised%20by%20the%20agents%2C%20these%2066%20passengers%20reached%20Dubai%20from%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Mumbai%20and%20Delhi%20between%20December%2010%20and%2020.%20As%20directed%20by%20the%20agents%2C%20these%20passengers%20boarded%20the%20Nicaragua-bound%20aircraft%20of%20a%20private%20airline%20at%20the%20Fujairah%20International%20Airport%20on%20December%2021%2C%20a%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20CID%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20CID%20has%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20to%20help%20it%20collect%20more%20information%20about%20the%20agents%20who%20had%20acquired%20Dubai%20visa%20of%20these%2055%20passengers%2C%20bank%20details%20of%20agents%20who%20had%20paid%20the%20visa%20fee%20from%20his%20account%2C%20how%20the%20agents%20managed%20to%20acquire%20visa%20of%20Nicaragua%20from%20Dubai%20and%20who%20booked%20the%20flight%20from%20Dubai%20and%20paid%20money%20for%20the%20tickets%20of%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chartered%20flight%2C%20which%20was%20operated%20by%20Romanian%20charter%20company%20Legend%20Airlines%20and%20bound%20for%20Nicaragua%2C%20landed%20at%20Vatry%20near%20Paris%20on%20December%2021%20for%20a%20technical%20stopover%20en%20route%20from%20Dubai%20when%20the%20French%20police%20intervened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20authorities%20launched%20a%20judicial%20investigation%20into%20the%20conditions%20and%20purpose%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20with%20a%20unit%20specialising%20in%20organised%20crime%20investigating%20suspected%20human%20trafficking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENicaragua%20has%20become%20a%20popular%20destination%20for%20those%20seeking%20asylum%20in%20the%20US.%20As%20many%20as%2096%2C917%20Indians%20attempted%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20illegally%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202023%2C%20signalling%20a%2051.61%20per%20cent%20jump%20from%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20according%20to%20data%20made%20available%20by%20the%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Patrol%20(CBP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2041%2C770%20of%20those%20Indians%20attempted%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20via%20the%20Mexican%20land%20border%2C%20CBP%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlights%20to%20Nicaragua%20or%20third%20countries%20where%20obtaining%20travel%20documents%20is%20easy%20have%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20'dunki'%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704198480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Ftqguu9ao_grounded-plane-afp-_625x300_26_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdonkey-flight-fliers-from-gujarat-agreed-to-pay-rs-60-lakh-to-enter-us-4787072%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%2060%20people%20from%20Gujarat%20on%20board%20the%20Nicaragua-bound%20plane%2C%20which%20was%20sent%20back%20from%20France%20over%20suspected%20human%20trafficking%2C%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20Rs%2060%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2080%20lakh%20to%20immigration%20agents%2C%20who%20promised%20to%20cross%20i