rc%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192233%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000176B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20the%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%2C%20has%20addressed%20allegations%20and%20criticisms%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20functioning%20and%20judgements%20%E2%80%93%20largely%20by%20doubling%20down%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArticle%20370%20judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five-judge%20bench%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20upholding%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20of%20Article%20370%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20lambasted%20by%20several%20experts%20and%20legal%20commentators%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-nariman-speech-election-commission-article-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%5C%22%3Eincluding%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judges.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20PTI%2C%20the%20CJI%20who%20headed%20the%20bench%20said%20that%20it%20would%20not%20appropriate%20to%20%E2%80%9Ceither%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20criticism%20or%20mount%20a%20defence%20to%20%5Bhis%5D%20judgement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20have%20said%20in%20my%20judgement%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20reason%20present%20in%20the%20signed%20judgement%20and%20I%20must%20leave%20it%20at%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20a%20judgment%20is%20public%20property%20once%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJudges%20who%20decide%20a%20case%20speak%20through%20their%20Judgement.%20Once%20a%20Judgement%20is%20delivered%20that%20judgement%20becomes%20a%20public%20property%20of%20the%20nation.%20Until%20a%20judgement%20is%20delivered%20the%20process%20is%20confined%20to%20the%20judges%20who%20are%20involved%20in%20the%20decision%20of%20that%20case.%20Once%20we%20arrive%20at%20a%20decision%20and%20the%20judgement%20is%20pronounced%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20public%20property.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20property%20of%20the%20nation.%20We%20are%20a%20free%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20are%20entitled%20to%20exercise%20their%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression.%20To%20critique%2C%20to%20criticise%2C%20to%20appreciate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESame-sex%20marriage%20verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20much-criticised%20judgment%20in%20the%20pleas%20for%20legal%20sanction%20to%20same-sex%20marriage%20by%20a%20bench%20headed%20by%20the%20CJI%2C%20he%20said%20that%20he%20has%20no%20regrets%20and%20that%20judges%20do%20not%20associate%20themselves%20with%20a%20cause.%20The%20bench%20refused%20to%20legally%20recognise%20same-sex%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20leave%20it%20for%20the%20future%20of%20our%20society%20to%20judge%20which%20course%20to%20take%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20minority%20view%2C%20the%20CJI%20and%20now-retired%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%20said%20that%20they%20do%20recognise%20the%20right%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20to%20enter%20into%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20told%20PTI%20that%20training%20teaches%20judges%20to%20distance%20themselves%20from%20the%20outcome%20once%20they%20deliver%20a%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COutcomes%20are%20never%2C%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20something%20which%20are%20personal%20to%20a%20judge.%20You%20decide%20a%20case%20based%20on%20your%20vision%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20on%20what%20you%20believe%20the%20vision%20of%20a%20just%20society%20for%20the%20future%20is%2C%20in%20constitutional%20terms%2C%20which%20is%20what%20I%20have%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAllocation%20and%20lawyers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20appeared%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20allegation%20by%20senior%20lawyers%20like%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20and%20Dushyant%20Dave%20on%20important%20matters%20often%20being%20reassigned%20to%20separate%20judges%20than%20who%20had%20already%20heard%20a%20part%20of%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20very%2C%20very%20clear%20in%20my%20mind%20that%20if%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20institution%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20to%20be%20maintained%2C%20we%20have%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20allocation%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lawyer-driven%20allocation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20allocation%20has%20to%20be%20according%20to%20%E2%80%9Cterms%20of%20our%20system%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20to%20trust%20your%20decision%20makers%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said%2C%20upholding%20the%20roster%20%E2%80%93%20which%20he%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20no%20lawyer%20can%20insist%20that%20their%20case%20will%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20particular%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20does%20not%20do%20justice%20either%20to%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20individual%20judge%20or%20the%20purity%20of%20the%20administration%20of%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAyodhya%20verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20said%20that%20the%20five-judges%20who%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20Ram%20temple%E2%80%99s%20construction%20on%20the%20site%20that%20had%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20on%20it%2C%20had%20unanimously%20decided%20there%20will%20be%20no%20authorship%20ascribed%20to%20the%20judgement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSupreme%20Court%20judgement%20on%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20was%20the%20judgement%20of%20the%20court%2C%20not%20any%20individual.%20So%20the%20author%20of%20the%20judgement%20was%20not%20named.%20It%20was%20a%20case%20of%20long%20conflict%20and%20diverse%20viewpoints%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20explanation%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSauravDassss%2Fstatus%2F1742033395645890943%5C%22%3Emet%20with%20some%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20commentators%20who%20have%20said%20that%20all%20judgments%20are%20those%20of%20the%20court%20and%20not%20of%20any%20individual%20%E2%80%93%20and%20must%20still%20correspond%20to%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20judges%20of%20that%20bench%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20occupy%20government-appointed%20positions%20after%20retirement.%20Justice%20S.%20Abdul%20Nazeer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fretired-sc-judge-s-abdul-nazeer-appointed-as-governor-of-andhra-pradesh%5C%22%3Ewas%20made%20the%20governor%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20who%20headed%20the%20bench%2C%20was%20made%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20soon%20after%20retirement%20and%20Justice%20Ashok%20Bhushan%2C%20who%20retired%20in%20July%202021%2C%20was%20made%20head%20of%20the%20National%20Company%20Law%20Appellate%20Tribunal%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704181402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192233%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000176B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcji-dy-chandrachud-article-370-supreme-court-ram-janmabhoomi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'What%20we%20have%20said%20in%20my%20judgement%20%5Bon%20Article%20370%5D%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20reason%20present%20in%20the%20signed%20judgement%20and%20I%20must%20leave%20it%20at%20that%2C'%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20told%20PTI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcji-dy-chandrachud-article-370-supreme-court-ram-janmabhoomi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Context%20Behind%20Rajnath%20Singh's%20Promise%20for%20'Justice'%20for%20Civilians%20Killed%20in%20Army%20Custody%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02125134%2FGCM2YvZbMAE8oG2.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDefence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20has%20visited%20the%20families%20of%20the%20Kashmiris%20killed%20in%20army%20custody%20and%20assured%20them%20of%20justice.%20He%20told%20them%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67825701%5C%22%3Eit%20was%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnobody%20can%20bring%20those%20who%20have%20died%20back%20to%20life.%20But%20there%20will%20be%20justice%E2%80%9D.%20This%20was%20a%20good%20thing%20to%20have%20said%20in%20humane%20terms%20and%20we%20shall%20see%20if%20justice%20comes.%20We%20should%2C%20however%2C%20examine%20the%20past%20record%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20(all%20governments%20including%20previous%20ones)%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20justice%20for%20those%20wronged%20by%20our%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20Special%20Powers%20Act%20(AFSPA)%2C%20the%20law%20that%20gives%20armed%20forces%20immunity%20in%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98disturbed%20areas%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%20We%20should%20try%20and%20understand%20it.%20In%202015%2C%20it%20was%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Disturbed%20Areas%20Act%20had%20lapsed%20in%20Kashmir%20in%201998%20but%20ASPFA%20was%20still%20in%20force%2C%20apparently%20without%20sanction%2C%20but%20this%20was%20overlooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20provision%20of%20AFSPA%20was%20the%20sweeping%20empowerment%20of%20individuals%20belonging%20to%20the%20police%20and%20the%20military%20and%20the%20paramilitary%20to%20open%20fire%20%E2%80%98if%20he%20is%20of%20opinion%20that%20it%20is%20necessary%20so%20to%20do%20for%20the%20maintenance%20of%20public%20order%E2%80%99.%20The%20forces%20could%20use%20force%20%E2%80%98even%20to%20the%20causing%20of%20death%E2%80%99%20and%20would%20be%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20for%20their%20actions%20except%20with%20the%20sanction%20of%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20could%20destroy%20anything%20they%20thought%20was%20a%20hideout%2C%20a%20fortified%20position%20or%20shelter%20from%20which%20an%20attack%20could%20be%20made.%20And%20they%20could%20arrest%20and%20detain%20without%20a%20warrant%20anyone%20they%20wanted%20and%20could%20use%20force%20in%20effecting%20the%20arrest.%20What%20happens%20when%20you%20give%20armed%20men%20such%20freedom%20in%20a%20place%20that%20has%20been%20declared%20hostile%20by%20the%20State%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20imagine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%201%2C%202018%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fwebsite%2Fstory%2Fin-20-years-centre-denied-prosecution-sanction-under-afspa-in-all-cases-recommen%2F307132%5C%22%3Ewas%20informed%20by%20the%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20defence%20ministry%20had%20got%2050%20requests%20in%2026%20years%20from%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20government%20for%20permission%20to%20prosecute%20soldiers%20under%20AFSPA.%20It%20granted%20permission%20in%20zero%20cases.%20These%20include%20cases%20of%20soldiers%20accused%20of%20unlawful%20killings%2C%20torture%20and%20rape%20between%202001%20and%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20Amnesty%20India%20report%20published%20in%202015%20looked%20at%20over%20a%20hundred%20cases%20and%20met%20with%2058%20families%20and%20found%20that%20since%201990%2C%20no%20sanction%20had%20ever%20been%20given%20to%20prosecute%20those%20accused%20by%20the%20Kashmir%20government%20of%20crimes.%20A%20chargesheet%20is%20the%20document%20filed%20after%20an%20FIR%20is%20registered%20and%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20investigation%2C%20meaning%20the%20police%20had%20found%20evidence%20of%20a%20crime.%20However%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20approved%20none%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20requests%20for%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20army%20says%20it%20conducts%20its%20own%20justice%20system%2C%20the%20court%20martial.%20These%20are%20opaque%20processes%20where%20the%20survivor%20or%20victim%20does%20not%20have%20access%20and%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20used%20for%20crime%20unrelated%20to%20military%20discipline.%20However%2C%20this%20parallel%20court%20system%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20soldiers%20trying%20fellow%20soldiers%20of%20crimes%20against%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fet-editorial%2Fpathribal-fake-encounter-case-indian-armys-acquittal-of-accused-soldiers-a-blot-on-democracy%2Farticleshow%2F29431106.cms%5C%22%3Eeditorial%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Edescribes%20what%20happens%20in%20these%20courts%20martial.%20The%20case%20discussed%20is%20related%20to%20an%20attack%20in%20March%202000%20during%20then%20US%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India.%20The%20army%20claimed%20it%20had%20attacked%20a%20hut%20which%20contained%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%20militants%20who%20had%20participated%20in%20a%20massacre%20of%20Sikhs%20in%20the%20village%20of%20Chattisingpora%20just%20before%20the%20Clinton%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2011%2C%202006%2C%20after%20investigating%20the%20case%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20filed%20murder%20charges%20against%20five%20serving%20army%20personnel%20from%20the%207%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20unit%20in%20the%20court%20of%20the%20chief%20judicial%20magistrate%20of%20Srinagar.%20The%20CBI%20argued%20this%20was%20a%20case%20of%20%E2%80%98cold%20blooded%20murder%E2%80%99%20and%20were%20not%20actions%20taken%20in%20the%20course%20of%20performing%20official%20duties%2C%20and%20so%20the%20perpetrators%20could%20not%20be%20protected.%20The%20Indian%20Army%20blocked%20the%20prosecution%20of%20five%20army%20personnel%20under%20Section%207%20of%20the%20AFSPA.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20upheld%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20action%20and%20asked%20it%20to%20decide%20whether%20it%20wanted%20to%20court%20martial%20them%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20the%20Quicksand%20of%20Counter-Insurgency%20Operations%20Has%20Hurt%20Indian%20Army's%20Core%20Value%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fhow-the-quicksand-of-counter-insurgency-operations-has-hurt-indian-armys-core-value%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Quicksand%20of%20Counter-Insurgency%20Operations%20Has%20Hurt%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Core%20Value%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202012%2C%20over%2012%20years%20after%20the%20murder%20of%20the%20five%20civilians%20in%20Pathribal%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20chose%20to%20bring%20the%20case%20before%20the%20military%20justice%20system%20and%20began%20proceedings%20in%20a%20general%20court-martial.%20On%20January%2024%2C%202014%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20said%20it%20was%20dismissing%20all%20charges%20against%20five%20of%20its%20personnel%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20evidence.%20According%20to%20the%20closure%20report%20filed%20in%20the%20Srinagar%20chief%20magistrate%E2%80%99s%20court%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20did%20not%20conduct%20a%20trial%20but%20instead%20dismissed%20the%20charges%20through%20a%20pre-trial%20procedure%20known%20as%20summary%20of%20evidence%20under%20Rule%2024%20of%20the%20Army%20Rules%201954.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20army%E2%80%99s%20self-acquittal%20of%20the%20Pathribal%20accused%20is%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%20cover%20ups%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Northeast%2C%20where%20the%20military%20has%20a%20free%20hand%20in%20dealing%20out%20%E2%80%9Cjustice%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20deems%20fit.%20This%20is%20a%20blot%20on%20our%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fdefence%2Fmacchil-encounter-life-sentence-of-5-army-men-suspended%2Farticleshow%2F59795490.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20paper%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20July%2011%2C%202018%20that%20soldiers%20were%20convicted%20of%20murdering%20three%20civilians%20but%20freed%20nonetheless%20by%20an%20army%20tribunal%20without%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20on%20December%204%2C%202021%2C%20soldiers%20from%20the%2021%20Para%20Special%20Forces%20army%20unit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fexclusive-army-officer-wilfully-suppressed-info-that-could-have-prevented-nagaland-killings-says-sit%5C%22%3Eshot%20and%20killed%20six%20coal%20miners%20in%20Nagaland%E2%80%99s%20Mon%20district%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20deaths%20led%20to%20violent%20clashes%20between%20local%20villagers%20and%20troops%2C%20and%20seven%20more%20civilians%20and%20a%20soldier%20were%20killed.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20soldiers%20killed%20another%20person%20after%20protesting%20villagers%20attacked%20their%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202022%2C%20Nagaland%20police%20filed%20charges%20against%2030%20soldiers%2C%20including%20a%20major%2C%20after%20a%20special%20investigation%20team%20found%20the%20military%20had%20used%20%E2%80%9Cwrong%20positive%20identification%20without%20proper%20application%20of%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20miners%20were%20shot%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20a%20clear%20intention%20to%20kill%E2%80%9D.%20On%20April%2014%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20denied%20permission%20to%20pursue%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20background%20and%20it%20is%20against%20this%20that%20we%20should%20judge%20what%20Rajnath%20Singh%20has%20said%20about%20the%20events%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Faakar-patel%5C%22%3EAakar%20Patel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704180646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fu