2%80%93%20the%20tribal%20Gujjars-Bakharwals%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Army%20because%20of%20which%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20ground%20intelligence%20on%20infiltration%20of%20foreign%20terrorists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20385px)%2085vw%2C%20385px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02114145%2FLieutenant_General_Deependra_Singh_Hooda_GOC-in-C_Northern_Command_Indian_Army.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22385%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02114145%2FLieutenant_General_Deependra_Singh_Hooda_GOC-in-C_Northern_Command_Indian_Army.jpg%20450w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02114145%2FLieutenant_General_Deependra_Singh_Hooda_GOC-in-C_Northern_Command_Indian_Army-288x300.jpg%20288w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691265%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERetired%20Lieutenant%20General%20Deependra%20Singh%20Hooda.%20Photo%3A%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGujjar-Bakharwals%20are%20nomads%20and%20have%20traditionally%20supported%20the%20Indian%20Army%20and%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20behind%20the%20roll%20back%20of%20insurgency%20from%20Jammu%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hooda%20said.%20Rukhsana%20Kausar%20KC%2C%20a%20young%20Gujjar%20woman%20from%20Upper%20Kalsi%2C%20had%20shot%20down%20a%20Lashkar-e-Toiba%20militant%20in%20Rajouri%20district%20in%202009%2C%20the%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2Fjan%2F02%2Farmy-should-win-back-gujjars-to-contain-militancy-2647040.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20seems%20to%20be%20some%20laxity%20in%20procedures%2C%20which%20may%20have%20developed%20during%20the%20long%20militancy-free%20period%20(Poonch%2C%20Rajouri%20were%20declared%20militancy%20free%20by%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20police%20in%202011).%20How%20much%20did%20we%20lose%20out%20on%20the%20local%20connect%20when%20nothing%20was%20happening%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20Army%20veteran%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20year%2C%20these%20nomadic%20communities%20move%20along%20with%20their%20herds%20of%20sheep%20between%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20and%20Poonch%2C%20Rajouri%20in%20Pir%20Panjal%20belt%20and%20carry%20very%20useful%20information.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20build%20back%20the%20old%20connection%20with%20the%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hooda%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Army%20needs%20to%20review%20the%20Standard%20Operating%20Procedures%20(SOPs)%20on%20counter%20insurgency%20operations%20in%20Poonch%20and%20Rajouri%20areas.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20stringent%20counter%20insurgency%20SOPs.%20Besides%20revamping%20ground%20intelligence%2C%20and%20investing%20in%20sources%20and%20assets%20who%20give%20us%20actionable%20intelligence%2C%20the%20Army%20needs%20to%20review%20the%20SOPs%20on%20movement%20of%20troops%2C%20whether%20they%20need%20additional%20troops%20in%20the%20region%20along%20with%20better%20protected%20bullet-proof%20vehicles%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hooda%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2Fjan%2F02%2Farmy-should-win-back-gujjars-to-contain-militancy-2647040.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fjk-families-affected-by-fake-encounters-view-poonch-civilian-deaths-with-doubts-and-despair%5C%22%3EJ%26amp%3BK%3A%20Families%20Affected%20by%20%E2%80%98Fake%20Encounters%E2%80%99%20View%20Poonch%20Civilian%20Deaths%20with%20Doubts%20and%20Despair%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20militancy-related%20violence%20and%20local%20recruitment%20had%20gone%20down%20significantly%20in%20Kashmir%20Valley%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fthree-army-soldiers-killed-in-anti-militancy-operation-in-jks-poonch%5C%22%3Emilitants%20seem%20to%20have%20shifted%20the%20focus%20seemingly%20towards%20Jammu%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20was%20a%20militancy-free%20region%20before%20August%205%2C%202019%20when%20Article%20370%20was%20read%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2021%2C%20an%20ambush%20by%20terrorists%20at%20Dhatyar%20Morh%20in%20the%20Surankote%20area%20of%20Poonch%20resulted%20in%20the%20death%20of%20four%20soldiers%20and%20injuries%20to%20three%20others.%20Following%20the%20attack%2C%20three%20people%20from%20the%20Gujjar%20community%2C%20who%20were%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20Army%20died%20in%20custody%2C%20leading%20to%20anger%20within%20the%20community.%20A%20video%20clip%20showing%20uniformed%20soldiers%20from%2048%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20torturing%20the%20men%20also%20surfaced%20on%20social%20media.%20Mobile%20internet%20was%20shut%20down%20after%20the%20incident%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20mitigate%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20unrest%2C%20on%20December%2024%2C%20the%20Army%20removed%20the%20brigade%20commander%20and%20three%20other%20officers%20of%2013%20Rashtriya%20Rifles.%20The%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20police%20also%20registered%20an%20FIR%20against%20unknown%20persons%20under%20Section%20302%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20for%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2027%2C%20Union%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20accompanied%20by%20Lt.%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20and%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%20General%20Manoj%20Pande%2C%20visited%20the%20Poonch%20sector%20to%20review%20the%20situation.%20During%20their%20visit%2C%20they%20also%20met%20with%20the%20families%20of%20the%20three%20deceased%20civilians%20and%20assuring%20them%20of%20speedy%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704176821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F23153648%2FEffect-44.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fgujjar-bakharwal-jammu-kashmir-army-general-hooda%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Gujjar-Bakharwals%20are%20nomads%20and%20have%20traditionally%20supported%20the%20Indian%20Army%20and%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20behind%20the%20roll%20back%20of%20insurgency%20from%20Jammu.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fgujjar-bakharwal-jammu-kashmir-army-general-hooda%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Given%20the%20Role%20of%20US%20in%20Blatantly%20Supporting%20Israel...'%2C%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20Returns%20Magsaysay%20Award%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02105905%2FFu4KfacaUAAe7et.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%202002%2C%20social%20activist%20and%20current%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Socialist%20Party%20(India)%2C%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20was%20recognised%20by%20the%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%20Foundation%20as%20%E2%80%98an%20Indian%20who%20followed%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20path%20and%20supported%20education%20for%20poor%20children%20by%20tapping%20the%20resources%20of%20the%20Indian%20diaspora.%E2%80%99%20His%20organisation%2C%20Asha%20for%20Education%2C%20has%2012%20chapters%20and%20takes%20on%20the%20mantle%20of%20educating%20under-privileged%20kids%20with%20a%20view%20to%20shaping%20the%20socio-economic-political%20future%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98In%20electing%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20to%20receive%20the%202002%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%20for%20Emergent%20Leadership%2C%20the%20board%20of%20trustees%20recognizes%20the%20empowering%20example%20of%20his%20commitment%20to%20the%20transformation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20marginalized%20poor%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20citation%20read.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20January%201%2C%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20announced%20his%20decision%20to%20return%20the%20award%20and%20the%20degrees%20he%20got%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20to%20protest%20against%20the%20role%20of%20the%20US%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20his%20statement%20in%20full.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20received%20the%20Magsaysay%20Award%20in%202002%2C%20a%20little%20controversy%20was%20created%20due%20to%20my%20decision%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20protest%20outside%20United%20States%20embassy%20in%20Manila%20against%20the%20impending%20attack%20on%20Iraq%2C%20immediately%20a%20day%20after%20the%20award%20ceremony%20in%20which%20the%20award%20was%20handed%20over%20by%20the%20Phillippines%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20then%20Chaiperson%20of%20Magsaysay%20Foundation%20had%20tried%20to%20dissuade%20me%20from%20participating%20in%20the%20protest%20on%20the%20pretext%20that%20it%E2%80%99ll%20harm%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20foundation.%20My%20contention%20was%20that%20the%20award%20mentioned%20my%20participation%20in%20a%20peace%20march%20in%20India%20for%20global%20nuclear%20disarmament%20from%20Pokaran%20to%20Sarnath%20in%201999%20and%20hence%20my%20anti-war%20position%20was%20well%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20honour%20the%20decision%20taken%20at%20a%20peace%20conference%20at%20University%20in%20Manila%20which%2C%20coincidently%2C%20concluded%20on%20August%2031%2C%20the%20day%20Magsaysay%20Awards%20were%20handed%20over%2C%20to%20stage%20a%20protest%20at%20US%20embassy%2C%20as%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20the%20conference%20as%20well.%20After%20the%20protest%20on%201%20September%2C%20a%20Manila%20newspaper%2C%20in%20an%20editorial%2C%20challenged%20me%20saying%20that%20if%20I%20was%20the%20principled%20man%20that%20I%20would%20like%20them%20to%20believe%20then%20I%20should%20return%20the%20award%20to%20the%20US%20embassy%20before%20returning%20to%20India%2C%20This%20made%20the%20decision%20easier%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20returned%20the%20cash%20component%20of%20the%20award%20from%20the%20airport%20which%20came%20from%20the%20Ford%20Foundation%20of%20the%20US%20but%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Chairperson%20of%20Magsaysay%20Foundation%20I%20said%20that%20for%20the%20time%20being%20I%20was%20keeping%20the%20award%20as%20it%20was%20named%20after%20a%20former%20popular%20Phillppines%20President%20and%20had%20been%20given%20in%20my%20country%20to%20personalities%20like%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%2C%20Vinoba%20Bhave%20and%20Baba%20Amte%2C%20whom%20I%20considered%20as%20my%20ideals.%20I%20had%20mentioned%20in%20that%20letter%20that%20if%20the%20Magsaysay%20Foundation%20ever%20thought%20that%20I%20was%20harming%20their%20reputation%20too%20much%2C%20I%20would%20be%20happy%20to%20return%20the%20award%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20the%20time%20has%20now%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMagsaysay%20Award%20is%20primarily%20funded%20by%20Rockefeller%20Foundation%20and%20the%20category%20in%20which%20I%20received%20the%20award%20is%20funded%20by%20Ford%20Foundation%2C%20both%20American%20foundations.%20Given%20the%20role%20of%20US%20in%20blatantly%20supporting%20Israel%20in%20the%20current%20offensive%20against%20Palestinian%20citizens%2C%20more%20than%2021%2C500%20of%20whom%20are%20dead%2C%20and%20still%20continuing%20to%20sell%20arms%20to%20Israel%2C%20it%20has%20become%20unbearable%20for%20me%20to%20keep%20the%20award.%20I%2C%20therefore%2C%20am%20deciding%20to%20finally%20return%20the%20award%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Funited-states-israel-palestine%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Is%20Part%20of%20the%20Problem%20in%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20would%20like%20to%20apologise%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Phillippines%20if%20they%20feel%20hurt%20because%20of%20President%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%E2%80%99s%20name%20associated%20with%20this%20award.%20My%20protest%20is%20only%20because%20of%20the%20American%20connection%20with%20the%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20return%20the%20Magsaysay%20award%20I%20also%20feel%20that%20I%20should%20relieve%20myself%20of%20the%20degrees%20I%20have%20obtained%20in%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20I%20am%20also%20taking%20a%20decision%20to%20return%20my%20Dual%20M.S.%20degrees%20in%20Manufacturing%20and%20Computer%20Engineerings%20to%20Syracuse%20University%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%20and%20my%20Ph.D.%20in%20Mechanical%20Engineering%20degree%20to%20the%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Berkeley.%20Incidentally%2C%20I%20was%20made%20conscious%20of%20involvement%20of%20US%20academic%20institutions%2C%20especially%20their%20engineering%20and%20science%20departments%2C%20in%20defence%20projects%20during%20the%20protest%20on%20Berkeley%20campus%20in%201991%20against%20the%20US%20war%20on%20Iraq%20launched%20by%20senior%20President%20Bush.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Professor%20Pravin%20Varaiya%20of%20Electrical%20Engineering%2C%20whose%20research%20area%2C%20Control%20Systems%2C%20was%20same%20as%20mine%2C%20and%20who%20was%20a%20participant%20in%20the%20anti-was%20protests%2C%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20I%20was%20also%20unknowingly%20part%20of%20the%20war%20machine%20of%20United%20States.%20Thus%20began%20my%20disillusionment%20with%20my%20research%20area%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20change%20my%20research%20area%20once%20I%20began%20teaching%20at%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20at%20Kanpur%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%20let%20me%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20I%20am%20not%20against%20the%20American%20people%20or%20even%20the%20country.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20the%20US%20is%20one%20country%20which%20respects%20the%20human%20rights%20the%20most%20and%20offers%20the%20best%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20but%20sadly%20it%20is%20true%20only%20within%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20the%20US%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20have%20little%20regard%20for%20human%20rights%2C%20especially%20of%20the%20third%20world%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-israels-supporters-in-the-west-are-no-friends-of-jews%5C%22%3EWhy%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Supporters%20in%20the%20West%20Are%20No%20Friends%20of%20Jewish%20People%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20respects%20justice%20then%20it%20should%20stand%20with%20the%20side%20facing%20oppression%20in%20any%20war.%20It%20took%20the%20correct%20position%20in%20the%20Russian%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20but%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Israel%20against%20Palestine%20it%20is%20inexplicable%20why%20the%20US%20chooses%20to%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20misfortunes%20and%20sufferings%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20overlooks%20the%20crimes%20of%20Israeli%20defence%20forces.%20Had%20it%20been%20any%20other%20country%2C%20it%20would%20have%20imposed%20sanctions%20against%20it%2C%20like%20it%20did%20along%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20against%20South%20Africa%2C%20when%20apartheid%20was%20still%20practiced%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20to%20take%20the%20hard%20decision%20because%20I%20think%20US%20is%20singularly%20responsible%20in%20encouraging%20Israel%20to%20continue%20its%20aggression%20against%20Palestinians%20contrary%20to%20the%20popular%20world%20opinion.%20It%20could%20have%20played%20the%20role%20of%20mediator%2C%20like%20it%20once%20did%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20negotiate%20peace%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%20Creation%20of%20sovereign%20state%20of%20Palestine%20and%20its%20recognition%20by%20United%20Nations%20as%20a%20full%20member%20is%20essential%20towards%20the%20solution%20of%20the%20problem.%20But%20it%20is%20strange%20that%20US%2C%20which%20not%20very%20long%20back%20handed%20over%20Afghanistan%2C%20much%20bigger%20in%20area%2C%20to%20Taliban%20on%20a%20silver%20platter%20knowing%20very%20well%20that%20it%20was%20jeopardising%20the%20civil%20liberties%20of%20common%20Afghans%2C%20especially%20the%20women%2C%20parrots%20the%20Israeli%20position%20about%20Hamas%20being%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20ignoring%20the%20fact%20that%20Hamas%20has%20won%20an%20election%20in%20Palestine%2C%20unlike%20the%20Taliban.%20I%20feel%20that%20it%20is%20time%20to%20call%20out%20the%20double%20standards%20of%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESandeep%20Pandey%20is%20General%20Secretary%20of%20Socialist%20Party%20(India).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704174604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02105905%2FFu4KfacaUAAe7et.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsandeep-pandey-magsaysay-award-return-israel-degrees%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'As%20I%20return%20the%20Magsaysay%20award%20I%20also%20feel%20that%20I%20should%20relieve%20myself%20of%20the%20degrees%20I%20have%20obtained%20in%20the%20US%2C'%20the%20activist%20wrote.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A89%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsandeep-pandey-magsaysay-award-return-israel-degrees%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%3A%20Western%20elites%2C%20not%20Ukraine%2C%20are%20Russia's%20true%20adversaries%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704174126000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106470912%2Cimgsize-100142.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-western-elites-not-ukraine-are-russias-true-adversaries%2Farticleshow%2F106470918.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106470918.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%20asserts%20that%20Western%20elites%20supporting%20Ukraine%20are%20the%20true%20adversaries%20of%20Russia