Url%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fxi-jinping-chinas-economy-china-and-taiwan%2Famp_articleshow%2F106465653.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Japan%3A%20At%20Least%208%20Dead%20in%20Earthquake%2C%20Rescue%20Efforts%20in%20Full%20Swing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02084011%2FGCyQzk5aYAAwU19.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%E2%80%99s%20meteorological%20agency%20lifted%20a%20tsunami%20warning%20on%20January%201%2C%20Monday%2C%20as%20authorities%20race%20to%20reach%20earthquake%20survivors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ishikawa%20prefecture%2C%20in%20the%20Noto%20region%20along%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-issues-tsunami-alert-after-major-earthquake%5C%22%3Ewas%20hit%20by%20a%20series%20of%20quakes%20on%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20largest%20of%20which%20was%20logged%20as%20a%20magnitude%207.6%20earthquake%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Geological%20Survey%20and%20other%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20eight%20people%20died%2C%20according%20to%20public%20broadcaster%20NHK.%20Other%20news%20media%20reported%20several%20were%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETsunami%20warning%20and%20alerts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20JMA%20had%20issued%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20tsunami%20warning%E2%80%9D%20for%20Ishikawa%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20northwestern%20coast%20of%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20island%20of%20Honshu%20was%20issued%20lower-level%20tsunami%20warnings%20or%20advisories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20broadcaster%20NHK%20warned%20torrents%20of%20water%20could%20reach%20as%20high%20as%205%20metres%20(16.5%20feet)%2C%20which%20is%20higher%20than%20the%203-metre%20threshold%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20tsunami%20warning.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20reported%20that%20smaller%20tsunami%20waves%20had%20already%20been%20confirmed%20to%20have%20reached%20the%20coastline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20said%20that%20as%20of%20Monday%20night%2C%20it%20had%20ordered%20more%20than%2097%2C000%20people%20in%20nine%20prefectures%20on%20Honshu%20to%20evacuate.%20Authorities%20later%20downgraded%20the%20major%20tsunami%20warning%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctsunami%20advisory%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20people%20were%20still%20urged%20to%20move%20to%20higher%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%E2%80%99s%20meteorological%20agency%20warned%20that%20a%2045-centimetre%20high%20(1.5%20feet)%20tsunami%20on%20the%20South%20Korean%20east%20coast%20can%20grow%20and%20continue%20for%20more%20than%20a%20day.%20The%20Hawaii-based%20Pacific%20Tsunami%20Warning%20Center%2C%20however%2C%20said%20later%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20tsunami%20threat%20has%20now%20largely%20passed.%E2%80%9D%20Emergency%20services%20in%20the%20far%20eastern%20Russian%20island%20of%20Sakhalin%20issued%20an%20alert%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20western%20coast%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20affected%20by%20tsunami%20waves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20also%20issued%20a%20tsunami%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20we%20know%20about%20the%20earthquake%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Noto%20region%20saw%20a%20rapid%20succession%20of%20earthquakes%2C%20starting%20with%20a%205.7%20magnitude%20tremor%20at%20around%204%3A06%20pm%20local%20time%20(0704%20UTC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%207.6-magnitude%20quake%20hit%20just%20four%20minutes%20later%20and%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20series%20of%20weaker%20tremors%20for%20around%2090%20minutes%2C%20said%20the%20JMA.%20In%20total%2C%20the%20agency%20recorded%2021%20quakes%20of%204.0%20magnitude%20or%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20spokesman%20Yoshimasa%20Hayashi%20said%20at%20least%20six%20homes%20were%20damaged%20by%20the%20quakes%2C%20with%20people%20trapped%20inside%2C%20while%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20households%20had%20no%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20media%20reports%2C%20buildings%20swayed%20in%20the%20area%20around%20the%20capital%2C%20Tokyo%2C%20on%20the%20central%20coast%20of%20Honshu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20have%20warned%20that%20more%20earthquakes%20can%20hit%20the%20region%20over%20the%20coming%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CResidents%20need%20to%20stay%20on%20alert%20for%20further%20possible%20quakes%20and%20I%20urge%20people%20in%20areas%20where%20tsunamis%20are%20expected%20to%20evacuate%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22zh%5C%22%3E%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E5%9C%B0%E9%9C%87%E4%BC%9A%E4%B8%8D%E4%BC%9A%E6%98%AF%E5%80%92%E6%A0%B8%E5%BA%9F%E6%B0%B4%E7%9A%84%E6%8A%A5%E5%BA%94%E5%91%A2%EF%BC%9F%E4%BD%86%E6%98%AF%E5%8D%83%E4%B8%87%E4%B8%8D%E8%A6%81%E5%8F%91%E7%94%9F%E6%A0%B8%E4%BA%8B%E6%95%85%E3%80%82%E5%9B%A0%E4%B8%BA%E4%B8%80%E6%97%A6%E5%8F%91%E7%94%9F%E6%A0%B8%E6%B3%84%E6%BC%8F%EF%BC%8C%E6%88%91%E4%BB%AC%E5%B0%B1%E5%8F%88%E5%BE%97%E6%AC%A3%E8%B5%8F%E8%A1%A8%E6%BC%94%E2%80%94%E2%80%94%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9C%E4%B8%80%E5%B9%B4%E5%90%8E%EF%BC%8C%E6%95%B4%E4%B8%AA%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C%E4%B8%80%E5%AE%9A%E4%BC%9A%E6%83%8A%E8%AF%A7%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E9%87%8D%E5%BB%BA%E7%9A%84%E9%80%9F%E5%BA%A6%E5%92%8C%E5%8B%87%E6%B0%94%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9C%E5%9C%B0%E9%9C%87%EF%BC%8C%E6%B5%B7%E5%95%B8%EF%BC%8C%E6%A0%B8%E6%B3%84%EF%BC%8C%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E7%BB%99%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C%E7%8C%AE%E4%B8%8A%E4%B8%80%E8%AF%BE%EF%BC%9A%E9%AB%98%E7%B4%A0%E8%B4%A8%E7%9A%84%E7%90%86%E6%80%A7%E5%85%AC%E6%B0%91%EF%BC%8C%E5%BF%AB%E9%80%9F%E5%8F%8D%E5%BA%94%E7%9A%84%E8%B4%A3%E4%BB%BB%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C%EF%BC%8C%E6%9C%89%E5%85%AC%E4%BF%A1%E5%8A%9B%E7%9A%84%E8%87%AA%E7%94%B1%E5%AA%92%E4%BD%93%E2%80%9D%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FJapan%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Japan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2Fearthquake%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23earthquake%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FNewYear2024%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23NewYear2024%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FylrfY2FALE%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FylrfY2FALE%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20%E6%A4%B0%E6%B1%81%E6%B1%81100%25%EF%BC%81follow%20back%20(%40Yeye36395198)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FYeye36395198%2Fstatus%2F1741848521874260116%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%201%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENuclear%20plants%20report%20no%20abnormalities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20government%20said%20no%20abnormalities%20were%20reported%20at%20the%20nuclear%20plant%20in%20the%20area%20and%20nearby%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%E2%80%99s%20Nuclear%20Regulation%20Authority%20said%20the%20Shika%20plant%20in%20Ishikawa%2C%20the%20closest%20to%20the%20quake%E2%80%99s%20epicenter%2C%20had%20already%20halted%20its%20two%20reactors%20before%20the%20tremors%20for%20regular%20inspection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishida%20said%20the%20government%20has%20set%20up%20a%20special%20emergency%20centre%20to%20gather%20information%20on%20the%20quakes%20and%20tsunamis%20and%20relay%20them%20quickly%20to%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20news%20conference%20was%20planned%20for%200910%20UTC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20a%20major%20quake%20and%20tsunami%20killed%20nearly%2020%2C000%20people%2C%20devastated%20towns%20and%20triggered%20nuclear%20meltdowns%20in%20Fukushima.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3Esupport%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20offered%20US%20help%20to%20Japan%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20earthquake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20close%20allies%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Japan%20share%20a%20deep%20bond%20of%20friendship%20that%20unites%20our%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20Biden%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20administration%20is%20in%20touch%20with%20Japanese%20officials%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%20stands%20ready%20to%20provide%20any%20necessary%20assistance%20for%20the%20Japanese%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjapan-rescue-operations-underway-after-earthquake%2Fa-67866429%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704165169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F02084011%2FGCyQzk5aYAAwU19.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-earthquake-ishikawa-noto%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Smaller%20tsunami%20waves%20had%20already%20been%20confirmed%20to%20have%20reached%20the%20coastline.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-earthquake-ishikawa-noto%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It%20is%20Easy%20to%20Blame%20Nehru%2C%20but%20His%20Decisions%20on%20Kashmir%20Were%20Borne%20Out%20of%20Pragmatism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F12133508%2FPrime_Minister_Jawaharlal_Nehru_addressing_a_public_meeting_in_Kashmir.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20one%20of%20the%20three%20princely%20states%20(the%20other%20two%20being%20Hyderabad%20and%20Junagadh)%20that%20did%20not%20accede%20to%20India%20by%20August%2015%2C%201947%2C%20when%20the%20British%20paramountcy%20lapsed.%20While%20the%20power%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20people%20in%20British%20India%2C%20the%20rulers%20of%20the%20565%20princely%20states%20had%20been%20given%20the%20option%20to%20join%20either%20of%20the%20two%20dominions%20%E2%80%93%20India%20or%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20force%20Hari%20Singh%2C%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20to%20accede%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20a%20tribal%20invasion%20was%20engineered%20by%20it%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20valley%20in%20October%201947.%20As%20the%20Pakistan%20army-backed%20tribals%20reached%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Srinagar%2C%20the%20Maharaja%20signed%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20on%20October%2026%2C%201947%20and%20asked%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20rescue%20his%20state%20from%20the%20invaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWrites%20Maroof%20Raza%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EWars%20and%20no%20Peace%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20news%20of%20this%20invasion%20coupled%20with%20the%20urgent%20appeal%20of%20Hari%20Singh%20for%20military%20assistance%20reached%20Delhi%20both%20Mountbatten%20and%20Nehru%20reacted%20with%20considerable%20speed%20to%20save%20what%20was%20left%20of%20Kashmir.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnehru-kashmir-article-370-rss-bjp-distort-history%5C%22%3ENehru%20and%20Kashmir%3A%20After%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20Order%2C%20BJP%20Attempts%C2%A0to%20Distort%20History%20Again%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20corroborated%20by%20M.J.%20Akbar%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3ENehru%3AThe%20Making%20of%20India.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAkbar%20writes%2C%E2%80%9DFortunately%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20understood%20what%20was%20happening%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20got%20the%20news%20and%20he%20wasted%20not%20a%20minute%20to%20his%20response.%20As%20it%20turned%20out%20if%20Nehru%20has%20dithered%20even%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20Srinagar%20would%20have%20fallen%2C%20and%20all%20would%20have%20been%20lost.%20Later%2C%20Nehru%20himself%20wrote%20to%20his%20sister%20Vijay%20Lakshmi%20Pandit%2C%20then%20Ambassador%20in%20Moscow%3A%20%E2%80%98If%20we%20had%20dithered%20and%20delayed%20by%20a%20day%2C%20Srinagar%20would%20have%20been%20a%20smoking%20gun.%20We%20got%20there%20in%20the%20nick%20of%20time.'%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20October%2027%20and%20November%208%2C%201947%2C%20several%20Indian%20military%20reinforcements%20managed%20to%20reverse%20the%20tide%20of%20the%20battle%20for%20the%20Valley.%20The%20raiders%20were%20soon%20in%20total%20retreat%20as%20the%20Indian%20Army%20entered%20Baramulla%20via%20Srinagar.%20It%20is%20now%20an%20accepted%20view%20that%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20winter%20snow%20prevented%20any%20decisive%20operations%20from%20taking%20the%20momentum%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%20up%20to%20Muzaffarabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01162414%2FPashtun_Tribesmen_Warriors_during_the_1st_Kashmir_War.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01162414%2FPashtun_Tribesmen_Warriors_during_the_1st_Kashmir_War.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01162414%2FPashtun_Tribesmen_Warriors_during_the_1st_Kashmir_War-300x240.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691204%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPashtun%20warriors%20from%20different%20tribes%20on%20their%20way%20to%20Kashmir%20and%20Gilgit%20during%20Indo-Pakistan%20war%20of%201947-48.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FPakistan%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2020%2C%201947%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20matter%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20against%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20tribal%20invasion%20of%20the%20Valley.%20Mountbatten%20had%20initiated%20this%20idea%2C%20and%20this%20was%20to%20be%20done%20under%20Article%2035%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Charter.%20After%20repeated%20attempts%20failed%20to%20get%20a%20reluctant%20Jinnah%20to%20talk%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20Nehru%20and%20Patel%20were%20forced%20to%20establish%20India%E2%80%99s%20bonafides%20over%20Kashmir%20in%20the%20UN.%20Their%20decision%20was%20backed%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20which%2C%20besides%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20included%20non-Congress%20stalwarts%20such%20as%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20Baldev%20Singh%20and%20Shyama%20Prasad%20Mukherjee.%20After%20the%20onset%20of%20summer%20fighting%20resumed%20with%20both%20sides%20seeking%20to%20consolidate%20and%20expand%20their%20footprint%20in%20all%20three%20regions%20of%20the%20state%3A%20Kashmir%2C%20Jammu%2C%20and%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20eventually%20on%20August%2013%2C%201948%2C%20that%20the%20Security%20Council%20passed%20its%20three-part%20Basic%20Resolution%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(a)%20It%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(b)%20It%20asked%20Pakistan%2C%20as%20the%20aggressor%2C%20to%20withdraw%20all%20its%20forces%20regular%20or%20irregular%20(from%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir).%20The%20resolution%20accepted%20that%20India%20could%20retain%20part%20of%20her%20troops%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(c)%20It%20called%20for%20a%20plebiscite%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20future%20status%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20shall%20be%20determined%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20final%20part%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20Resolution%20on%20a%20plebiscite%20was%20NOT%20binding%20unless%20the%20first%20two%20parts%20of%20the%20Resolution%20were%20implemented%2C%20which%20are%20a%20ceasefire%20and%20the%20total%20withdrawal%20of%20Pakistani%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20ceasefire%20was%20eventually%20accepted%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20once%20it%20realised%20it%20could%20not%20pull%20off%20a%20military%20victory%20over%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Security%20Council%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20August%201948%2C%20Nehru%2C%20an%20ethnic%20Kashmiri%2C%20who%20knew%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20topography%20like%20the%20back%20of%20his%20hand%2C%20allowed%20the%20Army%20to%20continue%20operations%20as%20long%20as%20it%20was%20advantageous%20to%20do%20so.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20November%201948%2C%20the%20Indian%20Defence%20Forces%20captured%20Dras%2C%20Batalik%2C%20and%20Kargil%2C%20thus%20securing%20the%20route%20to%20Ladakh.%20Simultaneously%2C%20they%20took%20Mendhar%20and%20linked%20up%20with%20the%20Poonch%20garrison%20lifting%20the%20year-long%20siege.%20India%20accepted%20the%20ceasefire%20only%20after%20the%20Army%20had%20completely%20secured%20Ladakh%20and%20Rajouri-Poonch%20sector.%20Balraj%20Puri%2C%20a%20well-known%20journalist%20who%20covered%20the%20Kashmir%20operations%2C%20has%20recorded%20for%20posterity%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20major%20cause%20for%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Army%20in%20clearing%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20of%20the%20raiders%20was%20the%20people%20and%20the%20terrain.%20The%20advance%20could%20not%20be%20maintained%20with%20the%20same%20ease%20beyond%20the%20Valley%2C%20where%20both%20the%20people%20and%20terrain%20were%20inhospitable.%20The%20martial%20communities%20of%20the%20area%20which%20were%20ethnically%20and%20politically%20closer%20would%20have%20put%20up%20stiff%20resistance.%20The%20switch%20from%20the%20role%20of%20liberator%20in%20the%20Valley%20to%20that%20of%20conqueror%20would%20have%20changed%20the%20character%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army.%20The%20military%20and%20political%20cost%20of%20attempting%20to%20conquer%20the%20area%20from%20Mirpur%20to%20Gilgit%20and%20Baltistan%20and%20retain%20it%20within%20India%20would%20have%20been%20prohibitive%20for%20India%20at%20that%20stage%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20would%20have%20lost%20us%20much%20international%20goodwill.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20argument%2C%20according%20to%20Raza%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20put%20to%20rest%20all%20the%20strategic%20speculation%20often%20indulged%20in%20by%20most%20Indians%20as%20to%20why%20the%20Indian%20Army%20did%20not%20initiate%20an%20operational%20drive%20beyond%20the%20Cease-Fire%20Line%E2%80%9D.%20There%20were%20other%20reasons%20too%3A%20tremendous%20shortage%20of%20ammunition%2C%20fuel%2C%20transport%2C%20and%20other%20logistics%20problems.%20Hence%20both%20taking%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20dispute%20to%20the%20UN%20in%20January%201949%20was%20the%20right%20decision%20in%20the%20prevailing%20circumstances%20of%20the%20time.%20It%20is%20easy%20to%20be%20wiser%20by%20hindsight.%20Even%20so%2C%20there%20was%20no%20better%20option%20when%20the%20infant%20country%20was%20facing%20many%20other%20serious%20problems%20%E2%80%93%20rehabilitation%20of%20millions%20of%20refugees%2C%20acute%20food%20shortage%2C%20deplorable%20state%20of%20the%20inherited%20economy%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20extremely%20well-researched%20book%2C%20based%20on%20declassified%20papers%2C%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%2C%201947%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Prem%20Shankar%20Jha%2C%20a%20former%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CNehru%E2%80%99s%20seemingly%20incomprehensible%20behaviour%20stemmed%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20keep%20not%20just%20the%20ruler%2C%20but%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20with%20India.%C2%A0%20Everything%20that%20Nehru%20did%2C%20especially%20his%20willingness%20to%20treat%20the%20accession%20as%20provisional%2C%20was%20geared%20to%20this%20purpose.%20Indeed%2C%20nowhere%20were%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20qualities%20of%20statesmanship%20more%20evident.%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20willingness%20to%20accept%20a%20ceasefire%20while%20a%20third%20of%20Kashmir%20was%20still%20in%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20hands%20was%20born%20out%20of%20the%20same%20type%20of%20farsighted%20calculation%E2%80%A6%20an%20awareness%2C%20honed%20by%20his%20own%20Kashmiri%20origins%E2%80%A6%20of%20the%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20dissimilarity%20of%20Kashmir%20Valley%20from%20the%20Muslims%20of%20Poonch%2C%20Mirpur%2C%20Muzzafarabad%20and%20Gilgit..%20once%20the%20raiders%20had%20been%20cleared%20from%20the%20Valley%2C%20the%20largely%20Hindu%20and%20Sikh%20town%20of%20Poonch%20safeguarded%2C%20and%20the%20road%20to%20Buddhist%20Ladakh%20cleared%20at%20Kargil%2C%20Nehru%20was%20no%20longer%20keen%20to%20pursue%20the%20war%E2%80%A6%20With%20the%20Sheikh%20opting%20for%20India%2C%20there%20was%20little%20likelihood%20of%20the%20state%20as%20a%20whole%20voting%20to%20join%20Pakistan.%20But%20if%20Pakistan%20did%20not%20vacate%20%E2%80%98Azad%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%20this%20would%20be%20a%20blessing%20in%20disguise%2C%20for%20the%20parts%20that%20would%20not%20have%20become%20reconciled%20to%20becoming%20a%20part%20of%20India%20were%20the%20ones%20that%20it%20had%20cut%20away%20%E2%80%A6%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20vision%20was%20therefore%20sound.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20this%20vision%20were%20his%20cabinet%20colleagues%20Patel%2C%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20Jagjivan%20Ram%2C%20Ambedkar%2C%20Baldev%20Singh%2C%20and%20Shyama%20Prasad%20Mukherjee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20cabinet%20also%20later%20endorsed%20the%20introduction%20of%20Article%20370.%20A%20journalist%20of%20repute%2C%20now%20in%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20wrote%20a%20decade%20before%20he%20switched%20sides%3A%20%E2%80%9CArticle%20370%20was%20viewed%20then%20as%20a%20victory%20for%20Indian%20unity%2C%20and%20not%20as%20a%20problem%2C%20as%20is%20being%20made%20out%20by%20the%20heirs%20of%20Shyama%20Prasad%20Mukherjee.%E2%80%9D%20Unfortunately%2C%20in%20the%20India%20of%20today%2C%20it%20is%20%3Cem%3EAsatyamev%20Jayate%20%3C%2Fem%3E(triumph%20of%20falsehood).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20a%20writer%2C%20an%20ex-army%20officer%2C%20a%20columnist%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20Freedom%20Struggle%20and%20Beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704162605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F12133508%2FPrime_Minister_Jawaharlal_Nehru_addressing_a_public_meeting_in_Kashmir.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fit-is-easy-to-blame-nehru-but-his-decisions-on-kashmir-were-borne-out-of-pragmatism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nehru's%20decisions%2C%20which%20were%20endorsed%20fully%20by%20his%20Cabinet%2C%20were%20aimed%20at%20keeping%20not%20just%20the%20ruler%20but%20also%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20with%20India.%C2%A0Those%20who%20fault%20Nehru's%20moves%20on%20Kashmir%20in%201947-48%20should%20know%20that%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20be%20wiser%20with%20hindsight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fit-is-easy-to-blame-nehru-but-his-decisions-on-kashmir-were-borne-out-of-pragmatism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Korean%20opposition%20leader%20stabbed%20in%20neck%20during%20visit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704161940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-lee-jae-myung-south-korea_6409726.jpg%3F20240102024508%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flee-jae-myung-south-korean-opposition-leader-stabbed-in-neck-during-busan-visit-13040705%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22South%20Korea's%20opposition%20leader%20Lee%20Jae-myung%20has%20been%20stabbed%20in%20the%20neck%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Busan%2C%20police%20have%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A157%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flee-jae-myung-south-korean-opposition-leader-attacked-and-injured-by-unidentified-man-officials-say-13040705%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Flee-jae-myung-south-korean-opposition-leader-attacked-and-injured-by-unidentified-man-officials-say-13040705%22%2C%22a